text_b_pos: His sister congratulated him.

text_a: Danny wanted  to  learn  how  to  make  fried  rice. His  friend  decided  to  teach him. His friend went to his house and taught him. Danny tried making it for himself.
text_b_pos: Danny did a great job.
text_b_neg: Danny hated girls.

text_a: Kim had been working extra hard for weeks. She learned of a promotion up for grabs at her company. It came with a new office and great benefits. Finally all her work paid off and she was offered the promotion.
text_b_pos: She was happy to get the promotion.
text_b_neg: She was sad to get the promotion.

text_a: Rob has never been on a rollercoaster. Rob's friends offered him a free ticket to six flags. Rob decided he may as well join. They all went and waited a long line.
text_b_pos: Rob had generous friends.
text_b_neg: Rob's friends were thoughtless.

text_a: I traveled to Washington DC to visit my boyfriend. We went many places around town. But one place I wanted to go was the White House. He took me to the White House, and I was so happy.
text_b_pos: We took the tour and enjoyed the history of the place.
text_b_neg: We left the White House abruptly and did not take the tour.

text_a: My two year old son refused to wear training pants. He always begged to wear a diaper. One day, out of frustration, I let him remain naked. He went to the potty and used it when I wasn't looking.
text_b_pos: Now I don't try to make him wear training pants.
text_b_neg: Child protection services removed him from the home.

text_a: Bob discovered his truck had a flat tire. He had never changed a tire before. He got out the tire jack and iron. He couldn't remove the bolts.
text_b_pos: Bob called someone to fix his flat tire.
text_b_neg: Bob drove his truck to the market.

text_a: Joey was camping with his friends. He wanted to start a fire to roast marshmallows. He found some sticks and logs in the woods. He used a match to light the logs.
text_b_pos: Then he roasted marshmallows.
text_b_neg: Joey hated camping.

text_a: I came into the library and took a seat. When I looked around, I noticed a kid. He was staring at me for a while. I became frustrated and got up from by seat.
text_b_pos: I asked him what his problem was.
text_b_neg: I didn't mind what the kid was doing.

text_a: Bryan wondered why his arms itched. He scratched his arms until they left scars because it was so bad. He finally went to the doctor and he found out he had poison ivy. The doctor gave him ointment and some antibiotics.
text_b_pos: Bryan went home relieved.
text_b_neg: Bryan went home in pain.

text_a: Joyce bought some fruit a week ago. It was part of her new year's resolution to be healthier. She forgot about it after a few days. Eventually a really bad smell took over her apartment.
text_b_pos: Joyce threw the fruit away.
text_b_neg: Joyce was happy with the new fragrance.

text_a: A man was running down a path in a state park. He came to a gate in the path. The gate looked low enough to jump. The man leapt as high as he could while running.
text_b_pos: The man jumped over the gate.
text_b_neg: The man went under the gate.

text_a: Jeremiah is looking for a part time job that can help him earn money. A sandwich shop employs him to give out flyers about their sandwiches. Jeremiah loves the job at first, because he likes meeting new people. Eventually he finds it tiresome to be outside so much.
text_b_pos: Jeremiah reconsiders career paths.
text_b_neg: Jeremiah continues to work outside.

text_a: Alicia liked where she lived. One day, her parents told her they were moving. She was very sad. On moving day she said goodbye to her friends.
text_b_pos: Then they moved to their new house.
text_b_neg: Alicia was happy to be leaving her old house.

text_a: Mac had a vegan friend coming for dinner. He groaned, knowing he couldn't make steak or hamburgers. Then he remembered an alfredo sauce recipe made with cashews. To his surprise, the sauce came out creamy and delicious.
text_b_pos: They all enjoyed the meal.
text_b_neg: He decided to serve meatloaf instead.

text_a: Billy had a toy ball. He would take his ball wherever he went. One day, he had to go to school. His mom took his ball away from him.
text_b_pos: Billy was very upset.
text_b_neg: Billy was very happy.

text_a: Arnold bought a new television. He paid cash. After a couple of weeks it stopped working. He tried to return it but had lost his receipt.
text_b_pos: Arnold was not allowed to return the television.
text_b_neg: Arnold kept and loved his television.

text_a: Sammy's coffee grinder was broken. He needed something to crush up his coffee beans. He put his coffee beans in a plastic bag. He tried crushing them with a hammer.
text_b_pos: It worked for Sammy.
text_b_neg: Sammy was not that into coffee.

text_a: Alex ran across town to get to a friends house. He didn't know his shoe was untied. He had ran for three block when it happened. He tripped on that shoelace of his.
text_b_pos: Alex resolved to always check his shoelaces before leaving.
text_b_neg: Alex next ran for a seat on the school board.

text_a: Holly was glad to be safely inside her house as the storm raged. She was watching the storm as she heard a loud crack. Lightning had hit a tree beside the house. She stared as she watched it fall.
text_b_pos: She was relieved that it didn't hit anything.
text_b_neg: She went outside to fly a kite.

text_a: Jane needed a new kidney. Only Bob was a match. Bob didn't know Jane, but that didn't matter. Bob gave Jane his kidney.
text_b_pos: Jane was very thankful of Bob's generosity.
text_b_neg: Jane was very bad at Bob.

text_a: Pablo likes to eat worms. He read a book in school on how to do this. He fries them in olive oil. He likes to do this at least once a month.
text_b_pos: Pablo enjoys worms and views them as a delicacy.
text_b_neg: Pablo does not enjoy eating worms.

text_a: Jess hated egg salad. When her friend's mother served it, she knew she had to eat it. Just as she was about to take a bite the family dog walked by. No one was looking so she lowered it towards the dog.
text_b_pos: The dog happily ate the salad.
text_b_neg: Jess decided to make egg salad.

text_a: Amy came home from school on her birthday to an empty house. She was upset that everyone had forgotten her special day. She walked sadly into the living room. Suddenly, her friends and family jumped out from their hiding spots.
text_b_pos: Amy grinned with delight.
text_b_neg: Amy walked out of the room and left the house.

text_a: Today is Jim's first day as a police officer. He was excited to meet his partner Tim. While on their beat, they made a traffic stop for failure to yield. The two men instructed the driver on proper road safety.
text_b_pos: Jim and Tim become good friends.
text_b_neg: Then Jim shot Tim.

text_a: Diana cleans offices buildings for a living. She washes toilets and scrubs floors. On Friday she was really sick and nauseous at work. She couldn't take the day off.
text_b_pos: She threw up in the toilet.
text_b_neg: She ate a huge lunch.

text_a: Gina's friend Tami had a folder she didn't want anyone else to have. Gina wanted one but didn't know where to buy one. Now Tami had a new Lisa Frank Trapper Keeper. Gina was jealous since she wanted one too.
text_b_pos: Gina checked on ebay and found one she could afford.
text_b_neg: Gina mowed the whole yard and had no help from anyone.

text_a: I recently went to the zoo with my friends. We met there and entered together. We saw lots of animals, such as giraffes, monkeys, and elephants. We even were able to feed the giraffes.
text_b_pos: After the trip, we went home very happy.
text_b_neg: We then left the market and went home.

text_a: Rachel adopted a cat over ten Years ago. Suddenly, the cat was acting more lethargic and losing weight. Concerned, Rachel took her cat to the vet. The vet told Rachel that her cat had developed cancer.
text_b_pos: The vet treated her cat's cancer the best they could.
text_b_neg: Rachel was excited to hear the news.

text_a: We had fruit flies in our home last year. We looked up various treatments. We tried red wine in bowls. When that didn't work we bought a special trap.
text_b_pos: We could even see the trap working.
text_b_neg: We put out more red wine bowls after the results we saw.

text_a: Hal and Judy were moving into a new home with their son. They spent the whole day packing everything up. When they were ready, Judy and the son travelled to the new home. Hal followed behind them with a moving van.
text_b_pos: Judy and the son arrived shortly before Hal.
text_b_neg: Hal turned around and went back to the old house to live alone.

text_a: Joe bought a skateboard with his savings. He took his new skateboard to the park to show it off to his friends. While doing a trick, Joe fell and broke his arm. He spent four hours at the hospital getting his arm set.
text_b_pos: Joe was in terrible pain.
text_b_neg: After he left the hospital, Joe went surfing.

text_a: Jill was a high school student. She dreaded having to go to class. One day, she decided to ditch school. Her parents found out the next day.
text_b_pos: Jill's parents scolded her for skipping class.
text_b_neg: Jill's parents took her to Disney World.

text_a: Flora's tooth started to hurt. She hated the dentist, so she tried to ignore it. The pain got worse and worse. Finally, Flora had to call for a dentist appointment.
text_b_pos: The dentist was able to make her tooth feel better.
text_b_neg: She was excited because she loved going to the dentist.

text_a: Ben was late for class. His teacher yelled at him. He came in late the next day. His teacher wrote a note to his parents.
text_b_pos: Ben's mother will now wake him  up  one half  hour earlier .
text_b_neg: Ben crushes his alarm clock and buys a chicken.

text_a: Jeremy's mother didn't approve of his lifestyle. When he was 21, Jeremy decided to move out. He found an apartment in a nearby state with a new job. After several Years he cleaned up, and finances his own life.
text_b_pos: Jeremy enjoyed being more responsible.
text_b_neg: Jeremy had to move back in with his mother.

text_a: Yesterday I went to toys r us. I had to get gifts for my cousins. I loaded my cart up. Thankfully I found out they had a sale.
text_b_pos: Because I'm a cheapskate it suited me well.
text_b_neg: I bought every mouse they had.

text_a: Logan and Maria decided to make a film together. They wrote the script and hired the actors. After a lot of work, finally the film was done. They invited everyone to come see it.
text_b_pos: Logan and Maria were proud of the film.
text_b_neg: Logan and Maria were ashamed of the film.

text_a: Joseph was at the library. He wanted a new book but had no idea what to get. With so many choices, he felt overwhelmed. He decided on a new method of choosing a book.
text_b_pos: He closed his eyes and picked one.
text_b_neg: Joseph went downstairs and got an ice cream.

text_a: I had a stroke in 2011. I spent 8 weeks in hospitals and rehab centers. The staff fed me oatmeal every morning. After I got released I kept eating oatmeal.
text_b_pos: Oatmeal became my favorite food.
text_b_neg: I hated oatmeal and didn't eat it anymore.

text_a: Tom was talking to his wife Becky who had a bad day at work. He decided to bring home her favorite meal as a surprise. On the way home from work, there was a lot of traffic. After getting the food, he arrived home much later than planned.
text_b_pos: But everything was okay as soon as they hugged and ate dinner.
text_b_neg: Tom decided to take a trip to the casino, he ignored his family.

text_a: Laurie is going to her first formal dance tonight. Her date picked her up and gave her a beautiful rose. Laurie wore a long sparkling dressed. They danced and had fun with all of their friends.
text_b_pos: Laurie ended the night by kissing her date.
text_b_neg: Laurie went home crying.

text_a: I decided to rent a movie when friends came over last night. After looking through selections we decided on horror. We picked a great movie and sat down with popcorn. It was really scarey!
text_b_pos: I had a hard time falling asleep that night.
text_b_neg: Overall I was dissatisfied with the night.

text_a: Dave wanted buy a gun. He went to the gun store and asked many questions. He looked at big guns and little guns. He decided he wanted to buy a big shotgun.
text_b_pos: Dave bought it and enjoyed his purchase.
text_b_neg: Dave was against the second amendment.

text_a: Kelly wanted to be in the Navy. She asked a recruiter about it. He advised her to complete an application. She filled it out and submitted it.
text_b_pos: The navy got back to her promptly.
text_b_neg: And the US army got back to her.

text_a: My daughter had her baby shower in our Boston home. She invited friends and family in the area. Her old college roommate lives in Hawaii. She decided to surprise my daughter by flying 4800 miles.
text_b_pos: My daughter was excited.
text_b_neg: My daughter was disappointed.

text_a: Lee knew her mom needed new gloves and could not afford them. So Lee began to knit a pair. She hurried to finish them by Christmas. Then she presented them to her mom.
text_b_pos: Lee's mom was proud of her daughter for being so thoughtful.
text_b_neg: Lee's mom threw the gloves at Lee and left the room.

text_a: Tommy recently landed a position on his school's Debate team. They were having a debate tonight. He was pretty nervous. When he got there, the entire school was watching.
text_b_pos: Tommy ended up doing well regardless of his nerves.
text_b_neg: Tommy started playing guitar.

text_a: Fred decides that he would like to start remembering his daily life. He goes to the local store and buys a diary. From that day forward, Fred records everything he does in his diary. Year's later Fred references the diary to see how he spent his time.
text_b_pos: Fred enjoyed reading stories from his past.
text_b_neg: Fred didn't like his diary.

text_a: Stephanie wanted to make applesauce. She decided to drive to the farm market to pick some delicious apples. As she was walking through the orchard she tripped and fell. She broke both of her wrists.
text_b_pos: Stephanie could not get up until someone found her.
text_b_neg: Stephanie pushed herself up with her hands.

text_a: Carl joined the military right after high school. He signed a short contract that put him on the front lines. His best friend was killed in front of him. Happiness became a foreign concept to Carl.
text_b_pos: Carl had to go to therapy for post-traumatic stress disorder.
text_b_neg: Carl hung out with his best friend when they came home.

text_a: When I first met Janice, she didn't know how to crack a walnut. I couldn't believe she had gotten this far in life without this skill. I offered to teach her many methods to crack nuts. She accepted.
text_b_pos: Janice is now an expert walnut cracker.
text_b_neg: Janice decided she didn't want to learn how to crack walnuts.

text_a: I had to take my son to the emergency room this summer. He was playing football with some friends and got hit in the head. He split his eyebrow open and we worried he had fractured his face. Thankfully, there was no fracture.
text_b_pos: He has a scar from the stitches.
text_b_neg: My son died and we buried him in the graveyard.

text_a: Rover liked playing fetch with his owner. One day his owner threw the ball too hard. It bounced across the street. Rover weaved through traffic with amazing skill.
text_b_pos: He fetched the ball and brought it back to his owner.
text_b_neg: He then ran away with the small ball.

text_a: I went to buy a new television last week. After finally picking one out I took it home. I noticed it was broken as soon as I got it out of the box. The screen was cracked.
text_b_pos: I returned the TV.
text_b_neg: I was happy with the TV.

text_a: John felt like he was coming down with a cold. It was very cold outside that morning and he felt terrible. He called into work and told his boss he was ill. Then John got up and had breakfast and felt better.
text_b_pos: John had a nice day off of work.
text_b_neg: John then felt sick the rest of the day.

text_a: Fred just bought some new patio furniture for his house. He built it and set it all up outside himself. That night there was a bad rainy storm. The next day Fred saw that the rainy had ruined his new furniture.
text_b_pos: He was disappointed.
text_b_neg: He was pleased.

text_a: Austin needed artwork for his apartment. He went to some art galleries downtown to get inspiration. Once he had an idea. He went online and bought some materials.
text_b_pos: Austin painted several pictures similar to what he had seen.
text_b_neg: Austin went to the park and played with his dog.

text_a: Jen's manager told her she needed to upload her resume. She realized her resume was not formatted properly. She transferred all of the content over to the proper template. Adding information on her latest job, she updated the resume.
text_b_pos: Then she sent it to her manager.
text_b_neg: Jen hated washing dishes.

text_a: Frankie was in love with a distant, aloof man. The man she loved was not very nice to her. He cheated on her with other people in town. Frankie left him.
text_b_pos: Frankie found another man.
text_b_neg: Frankie went to see a movie.

text_a: Nila's mom was diagnosed with stage four cancer. Nila knew her mom did not have a long time to live. Nila made sure to provide her mom with a good life until her death. Nila fostered many good memories with her mom and they were happy.
text_b_pos: Nila loved her mom.
text_b_neg: Nila did not care for her mother.

text_a: I decided to pay a visit to someone I've been dating online. I never seen her in person, but I trust her. The airplane flight took several hours. When I arrived at the hotel, she said she's in front.
text_b_pos: I walked in and saw her.
text_b_neg: I got on the plane and flew home.

text_a: Bobby needed to get home from work late one night. He decided that he was going to hail a taxi. When he was in the taxi he realized that he knew the driver. On the way home they chatted about things.
text_b_pos: Bobby found the time passed quickly.
text_b_neg: Bobby asked to be taken to a restaurant.

text_a: Brian was asked to watch his friends dog. They left a notebook to keep a log. He would update it with the times he went there. Right before he came back he left a message regarding their time.
text_b_pos: He was happy that his friends considered him trustworthy.
text_b_neg: He had to admit he didn't really like their cat very much.

text_a: Jim was mowing the yard when his mower got stuck on some metal. Jim looked closely at the metal and saw that it looked like jewelry. He took the piece of metal to an appraiser. The appraiser told him it was an old ring from an older civilization.
text_b_pos: Jim sold the ring for 1000 dollars.
text_b_neg: Jim threw the ring away.

text_a: Sean was born into an Irish immigrant family. He was always proud of his Irish heritage. His family kept customs, ate Irish food, and watched Irish sports. Sean saved up money and paid for a big trip to Ireland.
text_b_pos: He was thrilled when he was finally on his way to Ireland.
text_b_neg: Sean spent his saving on a new snowboard.

text_a: Ann is pregnant. She was very excited knowing this for she always wanted a baby. A couple months in, she had a miscarriage. She is deeply traumatized by it.
text_b_pos: Ann is heart broken.
text_b_neg: Ann is relieved she is not pregnant.

text_a: Sam was stargazing one night. Suddenly he sat bolt upright. He saw a twinkling, moving star! He ran to show it to his dad.
text_b_pos: His dad laughed because the star was really a jet with lights.
text_b_neg: Sam's dad was glad his son was interested in geology.

text_a: Rene was at the arcade with a couple of friends on a Friday night. He was getting ready to play a game but realized he forgot his wallet. His friend Jack noticed this and offered to let him borrow money. Rene appreciated his offer and took him up on it.
text_b_pos: Rene then played games.
text_b_neg: Rene told his friend to leave him alone.

text_a: Paula wrote a lot of spoken word poetry. Her friends were supportive even though it was bad. They invited her to a party. Paula started delivering some spoken word.
text_b_pos: Her friends applauded her poem.
text_b_neg: Paula tore up her poem.

text_a: Yesterday I went to the animal shelter. I have been in search of the perfect dog for my family. I fell in love with a dog named Toby. After introducing him to my cat we decided to take him home.
text_b_pos: My family all loved Toby.
text_b_neg: Toby told me that he doesn't like my cat.

text_a: Josh liked watching anime TV shows. When he criticized one of them, its fans got angry with him. Josh didn't understand why they couldn't accept criticism. Josh kept his opinions to himself.
text_b_pos: Josh then decided to watch anime by himself.
text_b_neg: Josh enjoys watching anime with others.

text_a: My nephew is a professional chef. While cooking for us at our house he decided to show off a bit. We videoed as he sliced an onion behind his back. We were amazed how quickly he chopped and didn't get cut.
text_b_pos: He is a fantastic chef.
text_b_neg: He is an awful chef.

text_a: When it was time to eat, Mother rang the bell. Dad and Bill knew that sound when they heard it. They dropped their yard work, carefully, and washed their hands. Mother was happy when they finally arrived in the house.
text_b_pos: The family sat down, and enjoyed a meal together.
text_b_neg: She then yelled for them to get back to work.

text_a: Mike bought a new bike to ride in his town. He cycled from his house to a friend's house. On the way he met a group of kids riding bikes as well. Neiter Mike nor the kids were wearing helmets at the time.
text_b_pos: Mike accidentally collided with the kids.
text_b_neg: Mike didn't like riding bikes.

text_a: Zeke was throwing a Halloween party. All his friends were dressing up. Zeke thought about being a vampire or a wizard. Then he decided on a scarier costume.
text_b_pos: Zeke dressed up like a skeleton.
text_b_neg: Zeke would dress up as a pumpkin.

text_a: Tim had dreams of becoming a great bodybuilder. He worked out every night to try to reach his goal. His hard work paid off and he earned a spot in a popular contest. He showed his skills, lifting more than 250 lbs.
text_b_pos: Tim was very determined.
text_b_neg: Tim had little determination.

text_a: Gina had taken her crying brothers ice cream. Now he was crying because he wanted it back. Gina refused and continued to eat his ice cream. Her mother poked her and made her give it back.
text_b_pos: Gina got in trouble.
text_b_neg: Gina's mom liked her behavior.

text_a: My cousin's had a terrible experience with their babysitter. They had a hidden camera. They found video of her shaking the baby violently. The baby is having major problems.
text_b_pos: They reported the babysitter to the police.
text_b_neg: They gave the baby sitter a good review.

text_a: Janey and Lynne decided to go to the movies. Janie wanted to see a comedy, but Lynne wanted to see a thrill. When they got to the movie theater, they decided to make a compromise. They chose an action movie that had both comedic and thrilling parts.
text_b_pos: They were both happy.
text_b_neg: They decided to go to Vegas instead.

text_a: Tim was failing math class. He knew if he didn't pass he would have to go to summer school. He studied hard and asked for extra credit. On the last day of school he found out he passed!
text_b_pos: Tim was thrilled.
text_b_neg: Tim was terribly disappointed.

text_a: I have a favorite pair of socks. Last week I was doing laundry. One of the two was lost. I looked everywhere and couldn't find it.
text_b_pos: Eventually it turned up.
text_b_neg: All my socks were accounted for.

text_a: I asked Sarah out on a date. She said yes. I was so excited for our date together. We went to dinner and then a movie.
text_b_pos: I got to kiss Sarah goodnight.
text_b_neg: I had a terrible time.

text_a: Bob went to the doctor. The doctor told him that he was overweight. Bob realized that he had to get in shape. He joined a gym and started to watch what he ate.
text_b_pos: Bob got in shape.
text_b_neg: Bob gained 50 pounds.

text_a: Ted loves to go to the movies. He sees almost everyone and votes at the Oscars. He has a big party for the Oscars and they all place bets. Ted almost always wins with the movies he chooses.
text_b_pos: Ted continues to watch several movies a week.
text_b_neg: He decides to stop watching movies.

text_a: We took a family vacation to the beach last year. I spent a lot of time reading with my mom on the beach. One day while reading, I got stung by a horrible beach wasp. My arm swelled and was painful, I almost had to go to the hospital.
text_b_pos: Eventually I healed.
text_b_neg: I found I loved being swollen.

text_a: Tori was so excited to go trick or treating. She put on her costume and ran out the door. She began to eat the candy as fast as she got it. Soon her stomach hurt.
text_b_pos: Tori fell ill because of eating too much candy.
text_b_neg: Tori felt even better afterwards.

text_a: Josie found a spider underneath her bed. She sprayed a can of lysol all around the bed frame. Josie saw the spider crawl up the wall. She swats the wall with a piece of paper.
text_b_pos: Josie hated spiders.
text_b_neg: Josie loved spiders.

text_a: Lary was a poor coal miner. Lary would work long hours every day in the mines. Lary was mining one day and saw a sparkle in the distance! Lary had found a vein of gold ore!
text_b_pos: Lary was happy and excited.
text_b_neg: Lary ignored it and kept working.

text_a: The Malamute always sniffed at the slide during his walk. His owner walked him up to the platform one day. He was scared to slide down. They continued to do this every day on their walk.
text_b_pos: The Malamute eventually tried to slide down the slide.
text_b_neg: The Malamute's owner never took him to the slide again.

text_a: Mark was running late to work. He tried to get their on time by driving over the speed limit. A traffic cop pulled him over. He was given a speeding ticket.
text_b_pos: Mark ended up being late for work.
text_b_neg: Mark was early for work.

text_a: Sal was jumping rope. Then he tripped and fell. He twisted his ankle as he went down. He needed to wear a brace for three weeks.
text_b_pos: Sal hated the brace.
text_b_neg: Sal was glad he decided to jump rope.

text_a: It was Nate's turn to sweep the floor this week. He was notoriously lazy. He decided to pay his roommate to do it for him. The roommate took the money and never did the work.
text_b_pos: Nate had a hard time working up the energy to confront him.
text_b_neg: Nate laughed with his friends about his dog's behavior.

text_a: I was bored when my daughter went to Kindergarten. I began to substitute teach at her school if a teacher was sick. I became very interested in why some kids have a harder time learning. This  led me to take a bunch of classes on special education.
text_b_pos: I began to teach special education.
text_b_neg: I decided to never teach.

text_a: Annie's grandfather needed a heart transplant. He was in the hospital for a very long time. When the transplant happened, her whole family was scared. However, he recovered with great health.
text_b_pos: Annie's family was glad about the outcome.
text_b_neg: Annie's family was sad.

text_a: Bob was daydreaming as he drove his car. A deer jumped out right in front of him on to the road. Bob's car slammed into the deer! The deer and Bob's front bumper were pulverized!
text_b_pos: Bob was dazed and had a cut on his forehead!
text_b_neg: After that, Bob was nervous about going horseback riding.

text_a: Grayson has collected stamps since he was a little kid. Now Grayson needs some money to help pay his rent. He thinks of his stamp collection. Sadly, he takes them into a pawn shop for sale.
text_b_pos: He gets much less for them than they are worth.
text_b_neg: Grayson uses the money from selling his stamps to buy a guitar.

text_a: My daughter brought her dog over to play with my dog. Her dog is big and full of energy. My dog is small, quiet and older. They are completely opposite.
text_b_pos: Both dogs enjoyed playing together, anyway.
text_b_neg: The cats made a mess out of the house!

text_a: Tina auditioned for her high school dancing team. After she danced, the instructor wanted to talk to her. He said that her skills aren't good enough to make the team. She immediately left the auditioning room.
text_b_pos: Tina held back her tears.
text_b_neg: Tina joined the high school dancing team.

text_a: Chuck loves this bar by his house. He goes there all the time with friends. He was on his way there one day and noticed it was closed. It had been put out of business.
text_b_pos: Chuck was upset.
text_b_neg: Chuck was happy that place finally closed down.

text_a: Lina has two kids. Lina was cleaning their rooms and realized their drawers were stuffed. She began to sort through the clothes. Lina had a big pile of clothes that were too small for her kids.
text_b_pos: Lina gave the clothes to charity.
text_b_neg: Lina made her kids wear clothes from the pile.

text_b_pos: Josiah crawled to his mother and took the toy.

text_a: After  gathering all of the items for our party, I invited our friends. Most of the were excited to come over for food! It took about an hour but they all arrived on time. After the arrived we began eating and enjoying ourselves.

text_b_neg: I couldn't wait for my friends to leave.

text_a: I was afraid of the exam tomorrow. Since the exam is tough, I decided to study all night. I decided to skip dinner just to have extra time. Ultimately, I was prepared on the exam day.

text_b_neg: I have negative memories of that time.

text_a: Mary needed to have teeth pulled. She wanted the dentist to put her to sleep. All he could do was numb the area with Novocaine. Mary stared at him in horror.

text_a: Two young women decided to go for a ten mile run near the AFB. Five miles into the run, they spotted a lone grey wolf with blue eyes. They tried to scare it away, but it kept moving toward them. The two women clambered up a tree and waited until other people came.
text_b_pos: The people chased the wolf away and the two women were fine.
text_b_neg: The two women fell off a cliff.

text_a: I noticed my hair was getting kind of long. I decided to try and get it cut that afternoon. Once I found a suitable barber, I dropped by for a cut. There wasn't a line, it was super quick!
text_b_pos: I really liked my new hair cut.
text_b_neg: He made the best sandwich in town.

text_a: Ron started his new job as a landscaper today. He loves the outdoors and has always enjoyed working in it. His boss tells him to re-sod the front yard of the mayor's home. Ron is ecstatic, but does a thorough job and finishes super early.

text_b_neg: Ron is immediately fired for insubordination.

text_a: Core broke her parents glass antique vase. She was afraid of being caught. She swept the glass under the rug. Her parents came and took of their shoes.
text_b_pos: Core's parents hurt their feet on the glass.

text_a: Jesus spent the day polishing the furniture. As night approached he surveyed the work he'd done. Everything looked shiny and new. Jesus invited all of his friends over for a party that evening.
text_b_pos: They said his furniture looked nice.
text_b_neg: His friends polished his furniture.

text_a: Joline went to the nail salon to get a manicure. The nail technician cleaned and trimmed her nails. Joline could not decide what color nail polish she would like. The nail technician suggested a design that used multiple colors.
text_b_pos: Joline decide to take the technician's advice.

text_a: The cat chased the mouse across the empty warehouse. Running in fear, the rodent moved as fast as it could. The larger feline stayed close behind. It was terrified.
text_b_pos: The mouse got away.
text_b_neg: The cat decided to lay down and take a nap.

text_a: Bobby folded his fruit roll-up into the shape of an airplane. He wound up his arm and threw roll-up airplane as hard as he could. It was far too heavy, though, and fell like a brick. Bobby decided that planes should be made out of paper.

text_b_neg: Bobby was thirty-five years old.

text_a: Jeremy has a distinct and strong personality. He had a bad time with his job and got fired. He spoke some unflattering things to his manager and co-workers. Since then, he's found it difficult to find a job.
text_b_pos: Jeremy has a difficult manner for the workplace.
text_b_neg: Jeremy's demeanor is perfect for the workplace.

text_a: Jaden was quite forgetful. He had not noticed that it was already Valentine's Day. Feeling rushed, he went out and got some flowers and chocolate. Jaden's girlfriend came home and found the treats.

text_b_neg: Jaden's girlfriend slapped in the face.

text_a: The football team had worked hard all season. They had won every game and made it to the championship. There were only seconds left on the clock and the game was tied. The quarterback through a long pass and the receiver scored.
text_b_pos: The crowd all stood up in their seats and applauded wildly.
text_b_neg: The crowd booed the team loudly.

text_a: Burke doesn't have many friends. He always walks around with a scowl on his face. One day, a stranger tells him that he should smile more. Burke decides to try smiling.

text_a: Glen was in the mood for a walk. He put on his jacket and went outside. While walking on the sidewalk, he tripped and busted his knee open. Glen stood back up and limped back to his house.

text_a: Sarah had an appointment to interview for a job. She put on her best skirt suit and headed to the interview. As she sat at the interview, Sarah noticed a run in her stockings. She was so focused on the flaw, she merely mumbled her replies.
text_b_pos: Because of her replies, Sarah didn't get the job.

text_a: Jim made spinach cookies. He sold them for five dollars each. No one bought any. However, at the last minute a man wanted twenty.
text_b_pos: He was surprised but thankful.
text_b_neg: Jim thought he was crazy and left.

text_a: Coming out of College, I was so nervous to start work. I could barely sleep the week before my start date. The day of, I was nauseous and jittery. However, a congratulatory text from my parents cheered me up.
text_b_pos: I had a great first day of work.
text_b_neg: I ended up leaving early because I was sick.

text_a: Bethany was self-conscious about her arm hair. She tried shaving it off. It grew back within a few weeks. She got a laser hair removal treatment.
text_b_pos: She felt better about herself.
text_b_neg: She wished it would grow back.

text_a: Tina was having her first skating competition. She was incredibly nervous. She was afraid something would go wrong. Thankfully she did great.
text_b_pos: Tina took second place in the competition.
text_b_neg: Tina has a baby blanket.

text_a: Mike had a free Saturday. He drove to several car dealers. He was interested in seeing potential future cars for himself. Mike found a Jeep he fell in love with.
text_b_pos: Mike bought the Jeep.
text_b_neg: Mike never liked Jeeps.

text_a: Ida had tickets to a two-day outdoor music festival. She was sad when it began to rainy on day one. But then she saw that other attendees weren't upset. They just danced in the rainy, so I followed suit.
text_b_pos: Ida was glad she could dance in the rain at the festival.
text_b_neg: Ida was glad that it didn't rain.

text_a: Cole was given coal for Christmas as a gag gift. Cole was young and took it very seriously. Cole was well-behaved for months after that. Eventually Cole forgot about the incident.
text_b_pos: Cole never got coal again.
text_b_neg: Cole thought about the incident every day afterwards,

text_a: Brad was sick with a cold! He wanted to go out and play! He was too weak to move. His mother gave him soup and medicine.
text_b_pos: Brad's mother was very caring.
text_b_neg: Brad's mother was rather uncaring.

text_b_pos: They gave him the antidote which saved his life.
text_b_neg: The doctor instructed him to drink plenty of fluids.

text_a: Laura decided to fly all the way to New York City. She flew specifically to get her hair done. She wanted her hair cut by a celebrity stylist. When Laura got it done she loved it.
text_b_pos: The compliments she got made Laura think the trip was worth it.
text_b_neg: Laura wore a hat all week to hide her hair.

text_a: Eve needed a new couch in her parlor. But she could not afford to buy one! Then she went to a secondhand store and found a great one. She had it delivered and set up in her living room.
text_b_pos: Eve thought the couch was very comfortable.
text_b_neg: She bought a new couch to replace it.

text_a: Thomas had been feeling under the radar lately. He went to his doctor to get a checkup. His doctor told him that his cholesterol levels were a little bit high. Thomas started eating healthier and going on walks.
text_b_pos: His doctor was very pleased at his next checkup.
text_b_neg: He was diagnosed with diabetes after gaining forty pounds.

text_b_pos: Jennifer stormed into his office and straightened her boss out.
text_b_neg: Jennifer thanked her boss for his fairness.

text_a: Sean was homeless. He begged for money on the streets. For one week, no one gave him money. He was starving.
text_b_pos: Sean decided to go to a shelter.
text_b_neg: Sean eventually moved to a huge house.

text_a: One day, Misty saw some something strange at church. Someone had left a beautiful, fluffy kitty on the church doorstep. Misty and her mommy took the kitty home and named him Huckle. Huckle proved a very funny kitty who liked to play with bags.
text_b_pos: Misty was happy to have adopted the cat.
text_b_neg: Misty did not want the cat.

text_a: Peter's friends invite him for a small Halloween party. He arrives late and hasn't had time to eat dinner. A friend offers him a slice of pumpkin pie at the party. The pie is delicious and it has whipped cream on the side.

text_b_neg: Peter was mad at his friend.

text_a: The high school student went to the dentist. She was told she needed braces again. She was not happy. She got braces and was in a lot of pain.
text_b_pos: But it was worth it when she saw her straightened teeth.

text_a: Jimmy went skateboarding this afternoon. It was the third time this week. He's getting good at it and really likes it. He fell once but hasn't given up.
text_b_pos: After all his practice this week, Jimmy has learned a new trick.
text_b_neg: Jimmy has decided to give away his skateboard.

text_a: Roy couldn't figure out why his apartment smelled so bad. His friends commented on it when they went over. Everyone decided to look for the source. It turned out to be an old fish in the refrigerator.
text_b_pos: Roy threw out the old fisher and everything smelled better.

text_a: Jen was invited to a Christmas party. She went with a close guy friend. They drank wine and talked with the couples that were there. As the group sang carols, Jen and her friend kissed.

text_b_neg: Beth was very happy during those two days.

text_a: When I was a kid, Google started for the first time. I remember asking my dad how to use the site. He showed me how to type and search anything I wanted. I became enthralled, and spent every day at my desk having fun.

text_a: Joe and his friends had their soccer game today. Joe was nervous. He was nervous if he would win or not. Finally after the game, Joe's team won.

text_a: Jeffries's remote ran out of batteries. It stopped working completely. He needed to replace them. So he went to the store to buy some more.

text_a: India wanted to try Iced Coffee. India decided to make her own Iced Coffee at home. India prepared the coffee in the machine for the beverage. India then grabbed the milk and ice for the beverage.

text_a: Oscar headed over to the nursery to find a tree to plant in his yard. He had a hard time deciding which tree to get. There were a lot of trees to go through. Finally, he opted on a Bonsai tree.

text_a: Our parents took us to Paragon Park in 1963. We took a ferry from Rowes Wharf in Boston. We rode the carousel, the whip, and the caterpillar. We played skeeball.

text_a: The cop pulled me over at night. He said I had been speeding. He went back to his car. I waited with the lights flashing behind me.
text_b_pos: I hoped he would just give me a warning.
text_b_neg: I enjoyed talking to the officer.

text_a: Cornelia had always loved working with her hands. She decided she wanted to try building a table by herself. She took a woodworking course to learn how to build it. After finishing the course, Cornelia built a beautiful table.
text_b_pos: Cornelia  uses it as a nightstand in her room.
text_b_neg: Cornelia chopped the  table  up  for  firewood.

text_a: Gina was in the middle of the backseat surrounded by siblings. They were driving out of town in heavy traffic. Gina looked out the window. In the next car a child was showing his mouth of chewed food.
text_b_pos: Gina was disgusted.
text_b_neg: Gina continued to stare.

text_a: A scientist discovers that there is a disease beginning to spread. He works on a cure for the disease in his lab. Other scientists gather to help him with his work. Several weeks go by and they manage to develop a cure.
text_b_pos: They save the world.
text_b_neg: They feel foolish for having done so.

text_a: Sara eagerly awaited December 1st to come. When it finally did she went to her shed and pulled out tons of boxes. Slowly she started unpacking them and organizing their contents. She then began decorating the outside of the house.
text_b_pos: She loved the lights.
text_b_neg: Sara loved the Fourth of July.

text_a: Christian's school was starting football tryouts. Christian decided to try out for the team. He practiced every day. He tried out for the team.
text_b_pos: Christian got on the team.
text_b_neg: Christian hates football.

text_a: Sharon had kept a bag of unknown seeds for Years. She decided one day to plant the seeds. Sharon put them in planters, believing they would be small plants. Sharon couldn't have been more wrong in her assumption!
text_b_pos: They ended up being huge plants.
text_b_neg: She cracked open a beer and took a swig.

text_a: Tyler wakes up and needs to shower before school. His little brother is using the shower. Tyler is worried he will miss the bus. Finally it is Tyler's turn to shower.
text_b_pos: Tyler takes a quick shower and gets to the bus stop on time.
text_b_neg: Tyler made cupcakes to show off his baking skills.

text_a: I was riding my bike to work one summer morning. I was a little late, so I was in a hurry. I was biking a little recklessly. To my dismay, my reckless biking caused me to get in an accident.
text_b_pos: From then on, I made sure to leave myself plenty of travel time.
text_b_neg: I knew then that I wanted to become a professional cyclist.

text_a: Pan tried to hit me for no apparent reason. As mad I was, I simply defended her punch. She continued to throw her fist at me. In efforts to stop her, I threw her on the ground.
text_b_pos: Pan finally stopped.
text_b_neg: I gave Pan a big hug.

text_a: Kelly and her friends went to a new ice cream shop. They were excited to try the new flavors. One of the flavors was wasabi. Even though it looked gross it tasted good.
text_b_pos: Kelly was glad she tried new flavors.
text_b_neg: She threw up.

text_a: Sal was nervous on his first day of high school. And as he sat in class, he felt intimidated by his peers. At lunch time, another student approached him. And that student felt the same way as Sal.
text_b_pos: Sal found out he wasn't alone.
text_b_neg: Sal found out no one felt like him.

text_a: My dad had just gotten a new car. To celebrate we all went for a drive. Another car ran a stop sign and crashed into us. I smacked the window hard enough to break it.
text_b_pos: I climbed out and me and my dad were ok.
text_b_neg: We were both flattened by the vehicle.

text_a: I waited in line all day to see a movie I knew I would like. I was so excited to see this movie. When I got into the theater, I was so excited I almost couldn't move. I watched the whole movie.
text_b_pos: I thought the movie was great!
text_b_neg: I left after the first forty five minutes.

text_a: Susie loves her grandma's banana bread. Susie called her grandma and asked her to send some. Grandma lived very far away. A week passed and grandma surprised Susie by coming to visit.
text_b_pos: Susie was so happy.
text_b_neg: Susie was upset.

text_a: Westin was getting married! He wanted his wedding to go perfectly. Everything went well until the evening. Someone got very intoxicated and fell into the cake!
text_b_pos: Weston and his wife kicked out the intoxicated person.
text_b_neg: Westin cut a perfect slice from the cake.

text_a: Yolanda hates roller coasters. Katie does not understand why. She decided to force Yolanda to ride one with her. Yolanda vomited all over Katie.
text_b_pos: Katie regretted forcing Yolanda to go on the ride.
text_b_neg: Katie was the happiest she had ever been.

text_a: Hannah was an amazing artist. She always had a natural gift. She decided to enter in an art competition. Thankfully she was able to win the top prize.
text_b_pos: Her parents were very proud.
text_b_neg: Her parents insisted that her grandmother did most of the sewing.

text_a: Joey worked for a great company but her hours were cut. The company said they had to let her go and laid her off. Joey began looking for another job right away. She had a hard time finding work but gave job searching her all.
text_b_pos: Joey finally received a call from an employer and got the job.
text_b_neg: Joey spent her days playing video games.

text_a: Bo and Jim wanted to drive fast. They took their cars to the salt flats in Utah. Bo hopped in his Mustang and Jim hopped in his Corvette. They raced each other for seven miles.
text_b_pos: Jim won the race in his Corvette.
text_b_neg: Jim gave Bo a massage.

text_a: Tony was tired of stale store bought bread. He called his mom and got her bread recipe. Tony gathered the ingredients that he needed. Tony baked the bread according to the recipe.
text_b_pos: It was some of the best bread he has had.
text_b_neg: Tony loved the pizza.

text_a: Ellen dreamed of winning a prize for her roses. She planned to enter her special purple rose at the fair. She fertilized the rose bush and covered it each night. The roses grew more beautiful every day.
text_b_pos: Ellen ended up winning the prize.
text_b_neg: Ellen had to pay a replacement fee for her library card.

text_a: Jackie had been a long distance runner for many Year's. Despite her very full iPod, she became bored with music. One of her running friends recommended an audible book. She loaded a new release to her iPod.
text_b_pos: She listened to a book while she ran.
text_b_neg: She was glad she is never bored of music.

text_a: I went on a blind date a few days ago. She was cute and friendly. We were set up through a co worker. We seem to have some things in common.
text_b_pos: Soon we were boyfriend and girlfriend and thinking of marriage.
text_b_neg: We broke up right away.

text_a: Larry has decided to help out his friends prepare for a party. He needs to bring a salad to the party. Larry slices tomato, lettuce, and other vegetables for the salad. When it is finished, he feels great.
text_b_pos: Larry was happy that he could contribute to the party.
text_b_neg: Larry decided to stay home from the party.

text_a: Bella sat by the campfire with her friends. They all had s'mores dangling over the fire, warming up. Each one of them took turns telling a scary story. When it was her turn she made sure to put her best acting to use.
text_b_pos: Bella's friends were very frightened by her story.
text_b_neg: Bella remained silent and skipped her turn.

text_a: Julie loved to read anything she could get her hands on. Most of her time was spent in the library. Her favorite library was staffed by Miss Watson. Miss Watson saw Julie's love of books and offered her a job.
text_b_pos: Julie happily accepted!
text_b_neg: Julie punched her friend in the eye.

text_a: Fred had his first karate tournament yesterday. He was very nervous. When it got there he was shaking. Thankfully he ended up doing well.
text_b_pos: He came in second place.
text_b_neg: Fred came in last place in his karate tournament.

text_a: Ralph hates shopping. His mom makes him go. They are there for a long time. Ralph helps his mom load and unload the groceries.
text_b_pos: He is surprised when his mom gives him money for helping.
text_b_neg: Ralph's mom punishes him for refusing to help.

text_a: Gary wanted to get Lisa's attention. One day he decides to write Lisa a Poem. The next day at school, Gary sees Lisa in the hallway. Gary gives Lisa a really big smile and hands her the poem.
text_b_pos: Lisa confesses she also has a crush on Gary.
text_b_neg: Gary slaps Lisa hard, and walks away.

text_a: While eating breakfast, I saw a lady. She was cute so I called her over. She sat down and we talked for hours. We really got along.
text_b_pos: I got her phone number.
text_b_neg: The woman told me to leave her alone.

text_a: Charles had a big, white dog. He did not like the way the dog looked. Charles thought about what he could do to change it. He painted the dog pink.
text_b_pos: Charles mother was very angry.
text_b_neg: He was very full.

text_a: George decided to buy a TV. He found a very nice TV that he wanted and went to pick it up. A few days later, George awoke to a surprise. His TV had been stolen.
text_b_pos: He told the police, who said they weren't likely to find it.
text_b_neg: Things had turned out just as he'd hoped.

text_a: Jon was thirsty. He didn't have running water in his house. Jon decided to go buy some water at the store. Unfortunately, he got into a car accident on the way.
text_b_pos: Jon regretted being thirsty in the first place.
text_b_neg: Jon was glad he left the house.

text_a: Darren was late to work and could not find his car keys. He looked all over his house. He asked his wife were they were. She told him to check his pockets.
text_b_pos: There were no keys in his pockets.
text_b_neg: Darren turned off the computer.

text_a: Joe was walking home one night. Out of nowhere, a man approached and stabbed him. Joe was badly injured! He staggered to the nearest hospital.
text_b_pos: It took him 2 weeks in the hospital to recuperate.
text_b_neg: He went straight to the cafeteria and had a long dinner.

text_a: Amy was going to buy coffee to beat her coffee crash. But there was no coffee machine in the school for kids. There was however a soda vending machine. Amy just needed to decide which soda had the most caffeine.
text_b_pos: Amy picked a Pepsi to drink.
text_b_neg: Amy decided to buy water.

text_a: Marcy received a valentine from her boyfriend. It was a card with a gift card in it for chocolates. She was happy and immediately ordered the chocolates. Her boyfriend came over and asked if she liked it.
text_b_pos: Marcy gave her boyfriend a big kiss and said yes.
text_b_neg: Marcy shrugged her shoulders and reached for the TV remote.

text_a: It snowed so hard that school was called off for the day. The boys put on their coats, hats, gloves and boots and went outside. They built a tall snowman and a snow fort. They had a snowball fight.
text_b_pos: They went inside to roast marshmallows.
text_b_neg: They took their clothes off to sunbathe.

text_a: Erica had to decide whether to take her final or go help friends. School was important to her, but her friend was in an emergency. Erica told her professor her situation. The professor said she could make up the final at a later date.
text_b_pos: Erica was so grateful that her professor was understanding.
text_b_neg: Erica told her professor that she was being unfair.

text_a: John was cooking dinner last night. He was making pork chops. Unfortunately, he dropped a pan and burned himself. He had to go to the hospital.
text_b_pos: John had a miserable evening.
text_b_neg: John had a wonderful evening.

text_a: Fred always stopped at the same coffee shop before work. He got to know the attractive barista. He developed a crush on her. Finally Fred worked up the courage to ask her on a date.
text_b_pos: She said yes.
text_b_neg: Fred told the barista to leave him alone.

text_a: Will was very wild in kindergarten, and did not listen to his teacher. His father was very upset with him. He pointed to the school janitor, and told Will that was his future. Will did not want to clean up the school bathrooms.
text_b_pos: Will started to listen to his teacher.
text_b_neg: Will wanted to be a janitor.

text_a: For the first time in my life I went to the opera. My girlfriends loves the opera and I don't. They were in town performing though so I told her I would go. To my surprise I actually had a good time!
text_b_pos: The performers were really talented and the music was beautiful.
text_b_neg: I went to the tennis match alone and had a beer.

text_a: Ben decided to treat himself to a coffee. He paid for the coffee using his debit card. Later, the bank called him saying he over-drafted. They explained that he had to pay a thirty dollar charge.
text_b_pos: Ben was frustrated at the extra charge.
text_b_neg: Ben was happy after getting the call from the bank.

text_a: Simon noticed a moving truck in front of the house next door. The family moving in had a teenage daughter and Simon was smitten. He worked up the courage to go over and introduce himself. She was shy but friendly and receptive enough to encourage him.
text_b_pos: He hung out with her all day.
text_b_neg: He yelled at her and went home.

text_a: John had just graduated high school, and was about to go to college. His mom helped him pack all his stuff, and he drove away. When he got there, he went to check out his dorm. His new roommate was there, and they hit it off.
text_b_pos: They walked around campus and got invited to a party.
text_b_neg: He thought college was going to be miserable.

text_a: It was a beautiful summer day outside. Bob decided to go for a walk at the park. Bob walked along the path and admired the scenery. He found a twenty dollar bill on the ground.
text_b_pos: He was happy.
text_b_neg: He was disappointed.

text_a: Jay was finishing up lunch at McDonald's, throwing away his trash. As soon as he threw it away, he realized there was a promo happening. There were some game pieces on his fry box so he fished it out. He peeled off the game piece and couldn't believe it.
text_b_pos: He'd dug in the trash for nothing.
text_b_neg: Jay thought Burger King was awesome.

text_a: The children were inside playing when they heard music. They ran to their mother and begged for change. She handed them a couple of dollars. They took off running outside, catching up to the ice cream truck.
text_b_pos: The children excitedly bought ice cream cones.
text_b_neg: The children threw the money in the street.

text_a: John wanted pizza, but he was broke. Then he remembered he had won a free pizza last week! He called the pizza place and gave them his code. They sent him his free pizza an hour later.

text_b_neg: John had carrots instead.

text_a: Ron was watching a high-speed chase on TV. The cop was chasing the bad guy through his neighborhood. It was terrifying! But then the cop caught the bad guy.
text_b_pos: Ron applauded the officer's performance.
text_b_neg: Ron started collecting bottle caps.

text_a: Amy always wanted to play the flute. The first day of band she told the teacher so. She practiced on her flute everyday for a week. It was terribly hard to play the flute.
text_b_pos: Amy was very committed.
text_b_neg: Amy showed little interest in the flute.

text_a: Gina's dad turned on the water hose for her. He watched as she sprayed the soda spill on the porch. It had been sitting there for hours. It was a dried gooey mess by the time she began cleaning it.
text_b_pos: Gina finally got it all cleaned after a couple of hours.
text_b_neg: Gina licked her plate clean.

text_a: Neil flew into Russia. There, he visited tourist sites and saw friendly locals. He found that Russia was colorful and vibrant. It also had a great and rich history.
text_b_pos: Neil found the trip stimulating.
text_b_neg: Neil found the trip dull.

text_a: Nick took his dog for a walk last Saturday. During the walk, his dog saw several other dogs. He was not well-socialized, so he started barking at them. It was a long and painful experience for both of them.
text_b_pos: Nick decided to take his dog to a trainer.
text_b_neg: Sam was very amused by his dog's behavior.

text_a: Jake wanted to make a YouTube account. He started vlogging. They did not get much attention. He then started doing skits.
text_b_pos: Many people viewed Jake's skirts.
text_b_neg: Jake hope no one would view his skits.

text_a: A girl falls in love with a boy and he liked her too. She finds out that their parents don't get along. The boy and the girl love each other so much. But, they don't want to hurt their parents feelings so they stay away
text_b_pos: But eventually they get together anyway.
text_b_neg: The boy and girl's parents are very happy they love each other.

text_a: Marina was walking past the library. She put her face down to avoid the harsh wind coming towards her face. All of a sudden a tumbleweed hit Marina's legs really hard. She looked down towards her legs but became disoriented.
text_b_pos: She couldn't believe how windy it was.
text_b_neg: She loved playing golf.

text_a: Tom bit into the Snickers bar and felt a jabbing pain. A small pebble in it made one of his teeth snap in half! He rushed to the dentist. Because it was an emergency, they saw him right away.
text_b_pos: The dentist fixed his tooth.
text_b_neg: Tom had so much fun that day.

text_a: Wendy landed her first job as a nurse at a nursing home. She really loved her job and connected with the residents. She really enjoyed talking to a little old lady in particular. One day, the lady showed her pictures of her children.
text_b_pos: Wendy enjoyed seeing the photos.
text_b_neg: Wendy ran out of the room crying.

text_a: Harry had just moved to England. His new friends kept telling him to try fish and chips. Thus, Harry decided to go to the market to get fish and chips. Harry loved the fish and chips!
text_b_pos: Sadly, they made him very ill.
text_b_neg: Harry thought the steak was delicious.

text_a: Tim was entering a baking contest. He decided to make his famous donuts. He made a big batch and entered them into the contest. The judges thought they were delicious.
text_b_pos: Tim won the baking contest.
text_b_neg: The judges vomited from the taste of the donuts.

text_a: Morgan loved tea. She bought a travel mug to bring tea with her to school. She drank all of her tea on the drive to school. So, when she got to school, she had to fill up with more hot water.
text_b_pos: Morgan was glad she remembered to bring extra tea bags with her.
text_b_neg: Morgan was glad the hot water tasted like coffee.

text_a: Ari's friends dared her to spend the night in the local haunted house. Ari tentatively agreed. She climbed in through the house's window. Then she snuggled up with her blanket in the corner.
text_b_pos: She lasted the whole night.
text_b_neg: She turned on the stove and made herself dinner.

text_a: Sue woke up in the middle of the night to an awful smell. She could not figure out what it was. She looked around the room. Then she noticed saw it.
text_b_pos: Sarah found spoiled milk on her desk.
text_b_neg: Sarah began to watch tv.

text_a: Tom wanted to go to a New York Giants game. However, the tickets were too expensive. Finally, he found tickets that were in his price range. He ended up sitting in the upper deck.
text_b_pos: He enjoyed watching the game anyway.
text_b_neg: Tom thought it was the best hockey game ever.

text_a: My husband and I rented a car on vacation. The car we got was horrible. The wipers didn't work, and a headlight was out. It smelled awful and was very dirty.
text_b_pos: We will never rent from that car company again.

text_a: Kayla borrowed a book from her sister. She brought the book with her to a coffee shop to read. Kayla accidentally spilled some of her vanilla latte on the book. She immediately went home to inform her sister.
text_b_pos: Her sister was mad!
text_b_neg: Kayla was an only child.

text_a: Tyler has been unemployed for Years. He has spent the last few months diligently applying for work. However, all of his applications are rejected. The rejections contribute to Tyler's feelings of desperation.
text_b_pos: He realizes he might have to apply for public assistance.
text_b_neg: He is thrilled about his new responsibilities at work.

text_a: My mom asked if she can borrow $100 dollars from me. Considering that she's broke, I loaned my credit card to her. The next day, my credit card was declined when I tried to buy food. The company told me that I made a $320 dollar purchase.
text_b_pos: I was angry at my mom for running up my credit card.
text_b_neg: I told my mom to keep using my credit card.

text_a: Lucy placed a pan of food into the oven. She set a timer and sat down to watch television. After awhile, she smelled smoke. Quickly, she checked the timer and realized it never went off.
text_b_pos: Lucy realized the meal was burned.
text_b_neg: Lucy realized the meal was perfectly cooked.

text_a: Sandy is Louie's mother. Louie is a puppy. A nice family adopted Sandy. They decided to adopt Louie too.
text_b_pos: The dogs seemed happy to stay together.
text_b_neg: Louie walked across the sandy beach, lonely.

text_a: Bob had a young puppy. The puppy loved to play catch with Bob. Of course, the puppy grew into a dog. The dog grew old and could no longer play catch.
text_b_pos: This made Bob sad.
text_b_neg: Bob was very happy about this.

text_a: Barry was excited that he finally registered to vote. He went to the polling place near his home. While walking into the building he noticed all of the campaign signs. He already knew how he would cast his votes.
text_b_pos: Barry voted.
text_b_neg: Barry turned around and went home.

text_a: Jake was trying to fall asleep. He had an important test tomorrow. He rolled around in his bed all night. He tried drinking a big glass of warm milk.
text_b_pos: Jake fell asleep after drinking the milk.
text_b_neg: Jake then drank a cup of coffee to stay awake.

text_a: Dan loves the sport of bowling. His dad taught him how to play when he was little. The use to compete in tournaments together. His dad has since passed away.
text_b_pos: Dan now bowls often to remember his father.
text_b_neg: Dan never liked to bowl anyway.

text_a: Lots of people were walking to class. They all wanted to get there fast. People started pushing others out of the way. They fell down.

text_b_neg: They all went back home.

text_a: Johnny's teacher treated the class to homemade snow cones. The teacher let each student pick a colored syrup topping. When his turn came, Johnny got mad when he saw only one color left. Johnny's teacher asked what was wrong.
text_b_pos: Johnny told the teacher he was upset he didn't get more colors.
text_b_neg: Johnny told the teacher he was happy.

text_a: Ellen had had four miscarriages in a row. Her husband Tim despaired of ever becoming a dad. Then the doctor called him at work. He told him that there was great news about Ellen.
text_b_pos: The doctor told Tim that Ellen was finally pregnant.
text_b_neg: The doctor told Tim that Emily went for a run.

text_a: Lina wanted to fry donuts. She got an application for the donut shop. To her delight, she had been hired! She started to go to work frying donuts.
text_b_pos: Lina loved her new job.
text_b_neg: Lina hated donuts.

text_a: The girls went to a bar. They opened a tab. They had a few drinks. They finally decided to close their tab.
text_b_pos: They went home talking about their night.
text_b_neg: They got into the plane.

text_a: Angie, an MTurk worker, saw herself as diligent. One day one of her favorite requesters rejected her work. Angie was very surprised and emailed them. They responded that her work hadn't been good enough.
text_b_pos: Angie tried to discuss the issue in detail.
text_b_neg: Angie decided to tell the requester to reject more of her work.

text_a: Bob picked up his glasses from the table. He slipped them in his backpack to wear at school. He needed them to see the board. In science he put them on.
text_b_pos: Bob was able to read the writing on the board.
text_b_neg: Bob enjoyed using his binoculars.

text_a: One night, a group of friends decided to play with a Ouija board. It was all in fun, and they played for an hour. After playing, they laid down for bed. Minutes later, they heard a strange banging sound on the floor.
text_b_pos: They all freaked out naturally.
text_b_neg: They slept soundly after that.

text_a: Johnson has never liked being outdoors very much. His girlfriend teases him that he could never go on a camping trip. Johnson decides to prove her wrong. He packs up a tent and goes camping for a long weekend.
text_b_pos: He had a miserable weekend, but told his girlfriend it was great.
text_b_neg: Johnson was an avid outdoorsman and hiked often.

text_a: Becky has a cousin named Ashley. Becky and Ashley used to be friends when they were kids. Ashley started being stupid when she grew up. She went to jail for stealing tampons from a dollar store.
text_b_pos: Becky lost contact with her.
text_b_neg: Becky is proud of Ashley.

text_a: James loved to challenge himself physically. He decided to begin training for a marathon. James began running every day before work. Finally James ran the marathon.
text_b_pos: James finished in the top 50.
text_b_neg: James was ashamed of what he had done.

text_a: Amayah's birthday is coming up. She will be five Year's old. Her mom is throwing her a princess party. She is invited a lot of her friends from school.
text_b_pos: Amayah is happy to be the princess at her party.
text_b_neg: Amayah is sad because she doesn't want a tea party.

text_a: Bill had just moved to a big city for work. He felt lonely because he did not know anybody in the town. After work one day Bill decided to join some coworkers for drinks. He had a lot of fun hanging out with them.
text_b_pos: Bill made a lot of friends that day.
text_b_neg: Bill was upset at his coworkers.

text_a: Jennifer dove from the starting block. She always felt that she held the rest of her team back. She pushed harder than she ever had to catch the other swimmers. She even past a few and actually placed second in her event.
text_b_pos: Jennifer was proud of herself for swimming so well.

text_a: Last week the internet went out. My wife and I were bored out of our minds. Every other option available seemed boring. Eventually we just drank and talked for a while.
text_b_pos: We ended up having a fun time after all.
text_b_neg: We were happy to not have Internet and to drink.

text_a: Last Tuesday I took my first spin class at the gym. It was the hardest exercise class I ever took. I worked through it for an hour and my legs went numb. When I got home my legs started to hurt and I couldn't walk.
text_b_pos: I went to bed and then rested until morning.
text_b_neg: I felt like I could run a marathon.

text_a: Tom and Cindy were eating marshmallows. But Tom began to get tired of it. Cindy suggested roasting the marshmallows. And Tom agreed with her suggestion.
text_b_pos: Tom enjoyed the roasted marshmallows.

text_a: Fred loved the amusement park but he never rode a roller coaster. His friends teased him that he was afraid of heights. One day at the amusement park he decided to face his fears. Fred rode the fastest and scariest roller coaster at the park!
text_b_pos: He was so happy that he did and loved the park even more.
text_b_neg: He decided to go home and cry.

text_a: My brother got a ticket. He never went to court. He eventually got pulled over again. They arrested him for failure to appear.

text_a: Helen lived in the state of Washington. Helen wanted to visit Canada. Helen's car broke down on the day of her trip. Helen decided it wasn't meant to be.
text_b_pos: Helen stayed home instead and planned to go another day.
text_b_neg: Helen had a wonderful vacation in Canada.

text_a: We bought a new cat post last week. The old one was very worn. Our cat is very picky. It the post is not made of sisal she will reject it.
text_b_pos: The cat accepted the new post made of sisal.

text_a: Gina went to her 6th hour class. It was gym. Gina hated gym, and all things related. She was horrified when the teacher made them run the first day.
text_b_pos: Gina cried at the end.
text_b_neg: Gina felt amazing that she ran.

text_a: It was summer and Gina and her sister were bored. They decided to watch music videos. There was the music video channel or the black entertainment channel. They chose to watch the black entertainment channel.

text_b_pos: Cara sat alone and cried.

text_a: Kelsi always wanted a new pool. She begged her parents for Years to get one. Finally they caved in and allowed her to have one. Kelsi was elated and could not believe it.
text_b_pos: Kelsi loved her new pool.

text_a: Andrew had never been in trouble for anything. His parents were out of town for the week. Andrew's friends came over and wanted to drink. So Andrew took out his parents secret stash of alcohol.

text_a: There was a major basketball game in the gymnasium. Me and my friend played on the same team. The game became intense and both teams were tied in the end. There was 4 seconds left on the clock and we needed to score.
text_b_pos: I shot the winning basket that won the game for our team.
text_b_neg: I walked off the court and never looked back.

text_a: One year, Matt was training for a half marathon. Near the time of the race, he slipped on a run and damaged his knee. Matt missed the race and required an extensive rehab. As soon as he could, Matt was back to training.

text_b_pos: James drove home to get change into dry clothes.

text_a: Ali went to a fast food place and paid with her credit card. The cashier took a very long time bringing her card back. A few days later, Ali found unusual transactions on her card. She called her bank, who reversed the charges.

text_a: Ann loved cake. Every saturday she would walk by the bakery. Ann loved to look at the beautiful cakes. One day a lady asked her to come inside.
text_b_pos: Ann came inside and watched as cakes were being made.
text_b_neg: Ann felt insulted by the lady's offer.

text_a: Joanie was interviewing for her first job. She was very nervous. She really wanted to get the position at the ice cream shop. She thought the interview went pretty well.
text_b_pos: The next day she got a call and was offered the job.
text_b_neg: She turned down the job when the manager offered it to her.

text_a: During the end of the week, I went to the local market. Since several items were for sale, I've looked at them. Some were vegetables and juice containers for a 50% discount. I took several of the items and went to the checkout.
text_b_pos: I liked getting a good deal.

text_a: Madeline was thrilled to get a new purse at Saks. Her mother took her to the bag department. Madeline immediately saw a pink bag she loved. She could not believe how amazing it was.
text_b_pos: Madeline's mother happily bought the bag for her.
text_b_neg: Madeline was upset with her new purchase.

text_a: Miss Jio called Nate's parents in for a conference. She said that Nate was disruptive and needed medication. Nate's parents went home and had a long talk. They took Nate to the doctor, who told them no medicine.
text_b_pos: The doctor suggested that Jake attend counseling instead.
text_b_neg: He gave the parents a prescription, which they filled promptly.

text_a: Bob was at the grocery store. At check out, he realized he forgot his credit card. The woman behind him offered to buy his groceries. Bob was so appreciative.

text_a: Jake's hair was getting a bit too long. He had a job interview coming up. He asked his mother to cut his hair. His mother gave him a nicely cut professional looking haircut.
text_b_pos: Jake got the job.

text_a: Zoey was taunted by her friends for having a strange name. She liked her name and wished people wouldn't be so mean. A new show was made that had a main character named Zoey. Zoey's name suddenly became very cool to her peers.
text_b_pos: Zoey was happy that everyone liked her name now.
text_b_neg: Zoey had her name changed when she turned 18.

text_a: Margie had a Christmas cactus. It never bloomed. She gave the plant to Desi. Desi took good care of the plant.
text_b_pos: The cactus flourished under his care.
text_b_neg: The goldfish were very happy and healthy.

text_a: Jan and Kim were both using the Montessori education model. Kim decided to take away all dragon and fantasy books from her kid. Jan was upset that Kim made this decision. Jan argued that imagination and fantasy was important.
text_b_pos: Jan brought the books back.
text_b_neg: Jan threw away the books.

text_a: Bill wanted to lose weight. He had been trying for Years, but lacked initiative. He finally stopped being so hard on himself. Growing in confidence, he met  his goals every week.
text_b_pos: He finally got down to his ideal weight.
text_b_neg: After a month he gave up.

text_a: Kristen was tired of her room. She need to move it around for a change. She hadn't moved it in over four Year's. After moving everything she saw a huge stain where her bed covered.
text_b_pos: She decided to put a rug over the stain.
text_b_neg: Melanie decided that the room looked perfect now.

text_a: Sherry liked to explore the outdoors. She decided to hike in the state park on a sunny day. While walking along a creek she saw something shiny. Bending down, she picked up the shiny item.
text_b_pos: It was a quarter.
text_b_neg: She picked up a knife covered with rust.

text_a: Ned wanted to learn to play basketball. He hung out in the school gym watching the team practice. Soon he felt confident enough to shoot a few hoops himself. The team watched him play and they cheered.
text_b_pos: Ned's skills improved as he practiced.

text_a: Jody was a very hard worker. She always did her best and often worked overtime. Jody's boss noticed her efforts and decided to give her a promotion. Her hard work had paid off!
text_b_pos: Jody became a manager and succeeded.

text_a: Ned was hiking in the woods when he saw a  lump of fur under a tree. The lump started to move, then emitted little cries. Ned moved closer and saw that it was a bunch of tiny baby possums. He called the local wildlife rescue and reported the baby possums.
text_b_pos: He waited until wildlife rescue arrived to save the baby possums.
text_b_neg: Ned went to the gym after work.

text_a: Alycia parked her car on the street and headed into town. She joined her friends and they had a great night. It got late, and Alycia's car seemed to not be where she left it. Before long, all ten friends had joined in the car finding adventure.
text_b_pos: Surprise they found it on the street she parked it.
text_b_neg: The friends found Alycia's truck.

text_a: Jason had always admired the fast movements of boxers he saw on TV. He started training to become a boxer in his spare time. He practiced jabs and jumped rope for hours each day. Finally he was a great boxer.
text_b_pos: He won his first fight by knockout.
text_b_neg: His wrestling matches were very exciting.

text_a: Ron had just found out that his family was moving to a farm. Ron was nervous. He knew nothing about animals. But when he got to the new home, he was surprised.
text_b_pos: Ron found that he rather enjoyed living on a farm.

text_a: Suzie decided to make her grandmother's spaghetti sauce. She made the sauce. She added mushrooms. She added the seasonings.
text_b_pos: Suzie tasted the sauce, and it was just right.

text_a: The teacher announced that there would be a pop quiz. The students let out a collective groan. This was the second pop quiz in a week. As the teacher began handing out the quizzes, the fire alarm rang.

text_a: It was autumn. Todd's yard was full of leaves. He decided he needed to rake them all up. Once he was done, he put them all in a bag.
text_b_pos: Todd put them out in the trash.
text_b_neg: Todd opened up the bag and spread the leaves around.

text_a: There were six puppies running around my foyer. It was going to be hard to choose the one we wanted to buy. Each of my daughters picked out a different pup. The owner said we could get a discount on two dogs.
text_b_pos: We each bought one dog.
text_b_neg: We did not like the dogs.

text_a: Jill was surprised when a handsome boy asked her to the college dance. As her roommates got ready, Jill fussed about her hair. Jill's roommates said they could help. Jill finished dressing into her toga-like white gown.
text_b_pos: Her date arrived and complimented her appearance.
text_b_neg: Jill and her friends had a fun girls-only night out.

text_a: Catherine has always been intrigued by the sport of Curling. Catherine loves watching the athletes play the sport on television. One day, Catherine decided she would visit a Curling practice session. At the practice, one of the athletes invited Catherine to play.
text_b_pos: Catherine then began to practice every day and got good at it.
text_b_neg: Catherine thought curling looked boring.

text_a: Lars had always wanted to try photography. His friend was an excellent photographer, but he had never tried. One day he bought a simple, but high quality, camera. From that day on, Lars shot images of nature every day.
text_b_pos: Lars fell in love with photography.

text_a: Felipe has always wanted to see the beautiful Pacific Northwest. He decided to travel to Oregon one day. In Oregon, Felipe hiked great mountains and ate delicious food. He was sad when his trip came to an end.
text_b_pos: Felipe immediately started planning the next trip.

text_b_pos: When he woke up, he had already landed.

text_b_neg: Flora felt forlorn because she never got to see Europe.

text_a: My friend Sharon was nervous yesterday. She found out her company wanted her to retire. Although she has a good pension, she was still nervous. I helped her rewrite her resume, preparing for a job search.
text_b_pos: Sharon is now looking forward to a new chapter in her life.

text_a: Samuel loved reading old science fiction stories. He collected books by HG Wells and Jules Verne. His favorite was HG Wells. His father gave him a copy of The Island of Dr Moreau.
text_b_pos: He loved it!

text_a: Lenny wanted to watch a movie. He drove to the local Hollywood video. Lenny rented three horror movies. Lenny went next door and bought a pizza from a shop.
text_b_pos: He went back home and binge watched all of his movies.

text_a: I went to go take a nap before work. As soon as I laid down the phone rang. It was my friend who wouldn't shut up about a new game he purchased. I lied and told him there was someone at the door.

text_a: Peter was excited for the class field trip. He was looking forward to visiting the science museum. The place had many cool exhibits and interactive displays. Peter was fascinated by the physics and space demonstrations.

text_a: Ashley got back her tax return. So she decided to go to the mall. Ashley and her roommate drove to the mall. They went from store to store trying things on.
text_b_pos: They bought lots of clothes.
