text_a: Sally forgot to each breakfast before she left the house yesterday. She debated whether to go back and get something to eat. She decided to pick up a meal on the way to work. She realized that she had no money in her wallet to buy breakfast.

text_b_pos: Sal felt great.

text_a: I started to binge-watch "Buffy the Vampire Slayer". After a few hours, I felt like running. Unfortunately, it was dark outside. I stood in the doorway for a while.

text_a: Ray went to a friend's house for a sleepover. He realized that he'd forgotten his toothbrush. He was unable to brush his teeth! Ray tried to use toothpaste on his finger, but it was no use.
text_b_pos: Finally, Ray  asked his friend if he had a spare toothbrush.
text_b_neg: Ray did a good job brushing his teeth.

text_a: There is a cemetery with 199 grave stones. 12 men brought a casket. 12 men put the casket in the ground. Men and women wept together.
text_b_pos: They mourned for losses.
text_b_neg: They rejoiced at the sight.

text_a: Harry went to the theme park with his family. His dad and brother rode on a big roller coaster with him. He then rode on some smaller rides with his mom. The family ate at a restaurant at the park.
text_b_pos: Harry had a great time at the park.
text_b_neg: Harry didn't like theme parks.

text_a: Last night we wanted to order a pizza. Half of us wanted pepperoni. The other half wanted sausage. I made a decision.
text_b_pos: We ordered a pizza with separate toppings on each half.
text_b_neg: I suggested we choose a different movie.

text_a: Sky went to Turkey with her class. She landed in Istanbul and started sightseeing. All the students loved the architecture. And they thought the food was great too!
text_b_pos: Sky never wanted her trip to end.
text_b_neg: Sky wanted to leave as soon as possible.

text_a: Brandon lives in Clearwater. He enjoys living by the ocean. A pier was built near his house. He decided to get his fishing license.
text_b_pos: Brandon then became a regular fisherman.
text_b_neg: Brandon then became a surfer.

text_a: John was excited to have a job interview. He went to the interview very prepared and nicely dressed. During the interview he was very talkative and likable. The manager of the company was really impressed by John's comments.
text_b_pos: The manager decided to offer John the job.
text_b_neg: John commented on how badly run he thought the place was.

text_a: Jim went to the wetlands with a giant gun. He set it up and waited for the geese to fly by. He shot into the flock. Two-hundred birds were hit.
text_b_pos: Jim felt pleased.
text_b_neg: Jim was frightened by his gunfire.

text_a: Tom was wrapping Christmas presents. But he lost track of who they were for. So he put wrong name tags on the presents. On Christmas, Tom handed his son a present.
text_b_pos: His son was bewildered when he unwrapped a dollhouse.
text_b_neg: His son got just what he wanted and was quite happy.

text_a: When I was five, I moved. I had to go to a new school. I felt lonely on my first day. A kid walked up to me and introduced himself.
text_b_pos: I felt less lonely.
text_b_neg: I felt more lonely.

text_a: Lauren finished her late night shift at the bar feeling tired. She usually liked taking the bus home from work. However, tonight she noticed that the moon looked beautiful. She strolled home happily under the bright moon.
text_b_pos: Lauren's husband was glad to see her feeling refreshed.
text_b_neg: Lauren wishes she took the bus home.

text_a: Tom liked to look at old cars. For his birthday, his family got him tickets to a classic car museum. Tom thought it was a wonderful gift. His family accompanied him to the museum.
text_b_pos: Tom loved his time at the museum.
text_b_neg: Tom told his parents he hated them.

text_a: I went to babysit my 5-year-old nephew in San Francisco. My sister encouraged me to bike her kid to school. I was afraid to bike across the city with my nephew in tow. Instead, we biked through Golden Gate Park to the beach and the zoo.
text_b_pos: We had a great time!
text_b_neg: I do not have a sister.

text_a: Benson was bullied at school by another boy. Benson began losing sleep about it. He finally told his teachers at school about it. The teachers approached the bully about the problem.
text_b_pos: The bully was expelled.
text_b_neg: They praised him.

text_a: One thing that Tina wanted to do in NYC was go to a hot dog stand. She finally saw a Nathan's stand and ordered a traditional one. The food tasted amazing. It was expensive but worth it.
text_b_pos: She was happy with the hot dog.
text_b_neg: She was sad about the hot dog.

text_a: Carla was worried that her daughter Ann was overextending herself. She'd seen her daughter's free time disappear with her new clubs. It all came to a head when Ann brought home a D on a test. Ann promised to work hard, begging to be allowed to stay in her club.
text_b_pos: Ann's mom said her daughter could choose one club if she studied.
text_b_neg: Carla told her daughter she needed to join more clubs.

text_a: Jenny's parents got divorced. Jenny and her mom moved to a tiny apartment filled with roaches. There was no stove, so they cooked chicken nuggets in a toaster oven. Jenny's mom ran out of money, so they went to a food bank.
text_b_pos: Jenny was unhappy.
text_b_neg: Jenny was thrilled with her new living situation.

text_a: Emily was at the beach. The weather started out tranquil. Suddenly the wind began to pick up severely. Anna was caught in a scary sandstorm!
text_b_pos: She was fortunately able to get back to the beach house safely.
text_b_neg: She had a wonderful time on the beach.

text_a: Bob was warm and tender towards his wife. He wanted to get her a very special gift for Valentine's Day. He asked all the people he knew what he should get her. They all had different opinions, leaving Bob confused.
text_b_pos: Bob finally went with his instincts and picked the perfect gift.
text_b_neg: Bob was never the same after being tasered by the mall cops.

text_a: I got a job as a shopping mall Santa last December. The hours were long. The pay was bad. But I found interacting with the kids to be completely amazing.
text_b_pos: I found that playing Santa was the best second job ever.
text_b_neg: I found that playing Santa was not worth my time off.

text_a: Jane was excited to go home early for once. She worked cleaning offices at night. She was ahead of her normal schedule. When she got to the final office she noticed a huge mess.
text_b_pos: Jane was disappointed she had to stay and clean the office.
text_b_neg: Jane was happy she had to stay and clean the office.

text_a: Lizzy lives on an island in the tropics. Everyday they go to the banana plantation and get some. Today Lizzy wanted to pick her own bananas. She climbed the tall tree and realized how big the bunches were.
text_b_pos: Lizzy needed help to get the bananas down.
text_b_neg: Lizzy decided she did not like bananas.

text_a: Sam wanted to throw a party. Sam invited all of his friends and neighbors. The party got extremely wild. All of the guests left the party in disgust.
text_b_pos: Sam had a terrible hangover the next day.
text_b_neg: Sam became a party planner.

text_a: Mark was a pro wrestler. He was getting ready for a big fight. He was nervous but practiced tediously. On the night of the fight he had won all rounds.
text_b_pos: Mark became famous and made a lot of money.
text_b_neg: Mark did not do well and felt defeated.

text_a: Fred went to the beach with his friends. He loved the water and the sunshine. His friends threw a party on the beach after the sun went down. Fred got drunk and passed out on the sand.
text_b_pos: Fred woke up with a hangover.
text_b_neg: Fred rolled over and fell off the bed.

text_a: Tine wanted to make the track team. She hoped she was fast enough. For a month before tryouts, she ran on her own. She rose early every morning to run for miles.
text_b_pos: Tine made the team with the best time of anyone.
text_b_neg: Tine sat on the couch and ate bonbons instead of trying out.

text_a: Jenny decided she needed a day off from work. She called in sick and went to the beach instead. She spent all day at the beach and got sunburned. The next day, her boss noticed that she was burned from the sun.
text_b_pos: Jenny was worried her boss would fire her.
text_b_neg: Jenny's boss gave her a raise.

text_a: I joined a fantasy football league for the first time this year. I joined my buddy's group because they needed one more person. I've never played before in my life. I ended up winning first place!
text_b_pos: I was very excited.
text_b_neg: I was very disappointed.

text_a: Ray hung a tire on a rope to make his daughter a swing. She climbed into it and played happily. Then Ray heard a loud, sickening crack, and a loud crash. The branch holding the swing had broken and his daughter had fallen!
text_b_pos: Ray ran to his daughter to make sure she was okay.
text_b_neg: Ray laughed at the crazy situation.

text_a: We went to Frank Pepe's pizza shop three weeks ago. The chain is quite famous in Connecticut. The chain recently opened in Boston. We went early to beat the crowd.
text_b_pos: We had a great pizza at Frank Pepe's pizza shop.
text_b_neg: We walked 5 growling dogs at the park across town.

text_a: Steve was very sad. Steve's girlfriend broke up with him. He decided to write a song to her. He poured his heart into the song.
text_b_pos: Steve wondered if they could ever get back together.
text_b_neg: Steve drove an hour away to go to a strip joint for drugs.

text_a: Jaris wanted to pick some wildflowers for his vase. He went to the state park. He picked many kinds of flowers. Little did Jaris realize that it was a national park.
text_b_pos: Jaris got in trouble and apologized profusely.
text_b_neg: Jaris picked flowers from a state park.

text_a: Mary wanted to make plans for New Year's Eve. She decided to have a party at her apartment. She invited all her friends. Her friends brought food and drinks to the party.
text_b_pos: It was the best New Year's Eve party ever.
text_b_neg: She accepted the food, and asked them all to leave.

text_a: Sam regretted not starting his history essay earlier. He typed up his closing paragraphs. All of a sudden, his screen was covered in a large blue error message. Sam shrugged and restarted his computer.
text_b_pos: He was disappointed in his broken computer.
text_b_neg: He was happy about his computer.

text_a: Don noticed a fly go into the living room. He decided to swat it. He tried for half an hour but it kept evading him. Eventually the fly flew out on its own.
text_b_pos: Don closed the door it flew out of.
text_b_neg: Don never went to the lake again.

text_a: Bob was really thirsty and wanted a soda. Unfortunately, he didn't have any money. Bob walked into a gas station and asked if he could have a soda. The cashier asked him if he had any money.
text_b_pos: He said no and left the gas station.
text_b_neg: He decided to go for a run.

text_a: Danny was working at the local ice cream shop this summer. He was very excited to have started his first job. On his first day a little boy dropped his ice cream on the floor. Without hesitation, Danny knew just what to do.
text_b_pos: He gave him another scoop of ice cream.
text_b_neg: He refused to give him another scoop.

text_a: Max was a very bright boy. But he would become lost in his own vivid imagination. No matter how hard he tried, he found himself daydreaming. Max did not do very well in school.
text_b_pos: Max consistently failed.
text_b_neg: Max's teacher's praised his creativity.

text_a: Charlie would eat anything. He was small, even for a chihuahua, but he loved food. His crowning triumph was when he stole a large pizza. Dismayed, his family rushed him a mean person they called Vet.
text_b_pos: Charlie changed his bad habits.
text_b_neg: The two then caused more problems.

text_a: Lynn told her friends they were going to sneak out. But sneaking back in was a problem. Her dad was in the kitchen. The girls climbed into the basement through an open window.
text_b_pos: Her dad caught them and scolded them for sneaking out.
text_b_neg: Her dad greeted them warmly as they arrived from their trip.

text_a: The old dog was doing worse than usual. He stopped eating and cried when he moved. Cheryl avoided making the appointment with the vet. She told her husband that she would make the appointment tomorrow.
text_b_pos: Cheryl loved the dog and prayed he would get better.
text_b_neg: Cheryl made more money turning tricks than at her full-time  job.

text_a: Nita was playing rummy with her dad. She had lost ten games in a row! They wagered their points on one last game. Nita played hard and well, and she won!
text_b_pos: Nita was so happy she finally beat her dad at rummy.
text_b_neg: Nita hated playing rummy.

text_a: Gina's family pulled into a rest stop off the highway. Gina got out and stretched her legs. At the stop there was a gas station and a Burger King. Gina normally didn't like Burger King's fries.
text_b_pos: Gina was so hungry that the fries tasted good this time.
text_b_neg: Gina walked down the highway without her family.

text_a: Neil wanted to see a historical spot on his trip to London. He took a bus tour to an old prison. It was called the Tower of London. Neil learned the history of the impressive tower.
text_b_pos: He was fascinated.
text_b_neg: He had a boring day.

text_a: I decided to go on a bike ride with my brother. We both headed out in the morning. We were having a lot of fun. Suddenly, he hit a rock and broke his wheel!
text_b_pos: I felt very badly for my brother.
text_b_neg: Watching my brother crash was fun.

text_a: Tami decided to attend volleyball tryouts. She was only in the 8th grade, but she knew she was good. She played hard and gave it her all. She hadn't anticipated the other players would be as good as her.
text_b_pos: All the players were good but she made the team.
text_b_neg: Tami made the basketball team.

text_a: Harry was doing his homework but had trouble with math. He decided to look for help on Youtube. After doing a few lessons, he saw an interesting video. The video was exciting and so he decided to watch another.
text_b_pos: Harry finally overcame the distraction and returned to his math.
text_b_neg: Harry decided math would be a great topic for a video game.

text_a: Dorothy's cat was pregnant. She didn't know how it happened. She convinced the family to keep the kittens. It wound up having 7 kittens.
text_b_pos: Dorothy made sure to buy lots of cat food.
text_b_neg: Dorothy went to the pet store and bought a new hamster.

text_a: Four Outlaws camped in Blood Gulch. They thought that they were safe, so they let their guard down. The sheriff was hot on their trail. He found them them early in the morning while they still slept.
text_b_pos: He arrested them.
text_b_neg: He let them go free.

text_a: My aunt is a nurse. She often talks about long hours at work. Last week was especially bad. She didn't have a single day where she didn't work late.
text_b_pos: It was hard work.
text_b_neg: It was easy work.

text_a: Everyday, I nag my daughter to do her homework. I finally decided that it is her own responsibility. Sure enough, she didn't do it one evening. I sent her to bed anyway, knowing she would get in trouble at school.
text_b_pos: She ended up making a bad grade on the assignment.
text_b_neg: She played basketball with her friends all afternoon.

text_a: Mark had a big interview for a new job. He prepared himself for the questions they may ask. The interviewer seemed to be impressed with Mark's answers. The interviewer informed Mark he had the job.
text_b_pos: Mark was very happy.
text_b_neg: Mark was enraged and stormed out.

text_a: Larry always wanted to feel stronger. He noticed that several students at school were lifting weights. Larry decided to lift weights as well. He started with light weights, but gradually tried heavier ones.
text_b_pos: Eventually Larry got stronger.
text_b_neg: Larry was ashamed of what he had done.

text_a: Sophie's nana was terminally ill. Sophie visited her in the hospital to say goodbye. Her nana gave Sophie her prized gold locket. She told Sophie to keep it to remember her by.
text_b_pos: Sophie cried.
text_b_neg: Sophie laughed in her face.

text_a: Sean and Sara were travelling to see a concert. They had to take the train to Portland. Once they got there, they checked into a hotel. They walked to the concert venue.
text_b_pos: Sadly, the concert was canceled due to sickness.
text_b_neg: They had a great time at the museum.

text_a: Helen got up for work early. It snowed the night before so she had to shovel her car out. It took her an hour to clear the snow. Heading back in the house to get ready, she heard a familiar sound.
text_b_pos: She had left the shower running.
text_b_neg: Helen went down to the lake to rent a jet-ski.

text_a: Ryan was at a park. And he saw a little girl holding a balloon. As he was leaving the park, he saw the same balloon stuck in a tree. He climbed the tree to retrieve the balloon.
text_b_pos: Ryan then found the girl and gave her the balloon she lost.
text_b_neg: Ryan then popped the balloon on purpose.

text_a: Amy wanted to get healthy. She purchased a smoothie blender. She made delicious fruit and vegetable smoothies. It took 20 minutes to clean the blender.
text_b_pos: Amy was determined to lose weight.
text_b_neg: Amy was determined to gain weight.

text_a: Neil was visiting Egypt. He took a tour to see the Great Pyramids. He stared up at them in awe. They were so huge and ornate!
text_b_pos: Neil was fascinated by the scale and beauty of the pyramids.
text_b_neg: Neil couldn't wait to get back to the hotel so he could watch TV.

text_a: Larry bought a new motorcycle. He was excited to look cool. The first time he tried riding it he dropped it. He hurt his leg and had to go to the hospital.
text_b_pos: Larry became careful.
text_b_neg: Larry loved going to the hospital.

text_a: Billy's friends thought that he was a scaredy cat. They dared him to go into the haunted house. He decided to go in and even stay the night there. Despite how scared he was he stayed the entire night.
text_b_pos: Billy felt brave.
text_b_neg: Billy demonstrated cowardice.

text_a: Monica decided to play Truth or Dare with her friends. They were all afraid to confess anything and only picked Dare. The Dares got progressively more elaborate as the day wore on. Monica dared a friend to shoplift doritos and the friend did it.
text_b_pos: Monica and her friends enjoyed the doritos before the next Dare.
text_b_neg: Monica could not explain why her friend had stolen the doritos.

text_a: Harold was a mailman doing his job. He had one package with a mysterious address. Harold looked all over town, but could not find the house. He went to his van and looked it up in his database.
text_b_pos: Harold found the address was correct but the city was not.
text_b_neg: Harold decided to throw the package away.

text_a: My daughter has a list of things to do before she turns 40. She is only 30. One thing was to read the Bible cover to cover. I decided to read the Bible again to support my daughter.
text_b_pos: I want my daughter to have a spiritual life.
text_b_neg: I want my daughter to stop being a Christian.

text_a: Janice usually wears jeans to work every day. However, now she has been promoted to manager. She decides she needs to dress a little more formally. Janice buys a few pairs of khakis for work.
text_b_pos: She also bought plenty of blouses.
text_b_neg: She wore a ripped shirt the next day.

text_a: Tuesdays are laundry days at my apartment. We have been too busy the last couple of Tuesdays. Now we have almost no clean clothes left. I'm dressed foolishly and still smell bad.
text_b_pos: I will do laundry right now.
text_b_neg: All my clothes smell great.

text_a: Sandra had always wished for a pet turtle. She told her parents she would be responsible for it. At first her parents didn't agree. Eventually Sandra convinced her parents she should get a turtle.
text_b_pos: She loved her new turtle.
text_b_neg: Sandra was upset that her parents refused to buy her a turtle.

text_a: Everyone in my family got together for Thanksgiving. It was a long journey for many, but they made it. We all sat together and ate dinner. After dinner, we visited and caught up.
text_b_pos: We had a great time.
text_b_neg: We all eventually couldn't stop arguing with one another.

text_a: Mike always had Golden Retriever dogs when he was growing up. Now that he had a steady job, he felt ready to have a dog too. Mike got a Golden Retriever and named him Spot. Now Mike and Spot take walks in the park every weekend.
text_b_pos: Mike loves his faithful friend Spot very much.
text_b_neg: Mike thought Spot was a strange cat, but he liked him.

text_a: Gina's dad pulled into the 24 hour Walgreen's parking lot. It was nearly 4 AM but everyone went inside. They needed toothbrushes before they went to grandma's house. It was Gina's job to pack them before they left.
text_b_pos: Gina felt guilty about forgetting everyone's toothbrushes.
text_b_neg: Gina's family was glad that their toothbrushes weren't packed.

text_a: Ava was mad that she had to wear a vest in the pool. She wanted to swim without a vest like her brother. She asked her mother if she could take swimming lessons. Ava took lessons for 6 weeks and learned how to swim.
text_b_pos: She was happy that she didn't have to wear a vest anymore.
text_b_neg: She was upset that she didn't have to wear the vest anymore.

text_a: Lewis knew the cave like the back of his hand. Five first-time cavers walked behind him. Suddenly, a few bats flew down from the darkness above. All the people but Lewis ran back towards the cave's entrance.
text_b_pos: Lewis laughed and told them not be afraid of the bats.
text_b_neg: Lewis started to dance.

text_a: Anna had a saltwater fish tank. She only kept coral in it. Then she decided she wanted some fish, too. She bought a few small clownfish and triggers.
text_b_pos: Now Anna has a diverse tank with fish and coral.
text_b_neg: Anna soon returned the fish to the store.

text_a: Amber had been working a lot lately. It was stressing her out a great deal due to other personal issues. She had been dying for a day off to relax. On her day off she hung out with boyfriend Rob
text_b_pos: They relaxed all day and Amber felt much better.
text_b_neg: Amber could not find anytime to relax.

text_a: I was at the park the other day. I walked near the lake and saw some ducks. I decided to throw them some bread. They chased after me in an angry fashion.
text_b_pos: I ran away from the ducks.
text_b_neg: The ducks liked me a lot.

text_a: Jake is one of my roommates. He took a gap year last year to work as a chef in Australia. Since the dining hall food was subpar we decided to cook. He taught me how to cook and season a steak.
text_b_pos: Jake has kept all of us well-fed all year.
text_b_neg: Now we all go to the dining hall instead of cooking.

text_a: Lester has always wanted to be more artistic. He decides to try to draw a picture of a flower one day. He sits in front of a beautiful orchid and begins to draw. Lester's drawing comes out very well.
text_b_pos: He hangs the picture on the wall in his living room.
text_b_neg: He decides never to draw anything again.

text_a: Harrison was playing a game of volleyball with friends. He hit the ball over the net and scored a point. However emily, on the opposing team also scored. The game was tied, until Harrison scored the winning point.
text_b_pos: Harrison was happy and excited.
text_b_neg: Harrison got angry with Emily.

text_a: Jill had to attend a dancing class around 8 P.M. He got ready and drove to the meeting place. He was only of the first people to audition. After his performance, the judges were impressed.
text_b_pos: He received many awards for his dance performances.
text_b_neg: He awaited a call back, but he never heard from the judges again.

text_a: I got my concert tickets. I drove to Chicago. I could not believe I was seeing a Beatle. I was 30 rows from the front of the stage.
text_b_pos: I cheered when the Beatle came under the spotlight.
text_b_neg: I began to tremble uncontrollably with terror and dread.

text_a: Anna wanted a banana milkshake. Her local ice cream shop didn't have that flavor. She went home and got out her blender. Then she added her own bananas and ice cream.
text_b_pos: Anna thought her own milkshake tasted just as delicious.
text_b_neg: Anna thought the chocolate shake tasted dreadful.

text_a: Boris was addicted to video games. His mother was concerned. She called a psychologist to get help. The psychologist tried to convince Boris to stop his addiction.
text_b_pos: Boris realized he was wasting his life.
text_b_neg: Boris decided to wear the dress.

text_a: Ted always wanted to be a senator. He finally got the chance to run. He was eager to make a difference. Unfortunately a personal issue derailed his campaign.
text_b_pos: Ted decided to run for county magistrate a year later.
text_b_neg: Ted's friends thought he would run in the campaign uncontested.

text_a: My roommate got a new job at the place I go to school. We decided to ride to work together. We got in the car and headed out together. The ride seemed much shorter with someone to talk to.
text_b_pos: When the ride was over, we parted ways.
text_b_neg: I did not have anyone to talk to though.

text_a: Carly was waiting for Sam to call her. He promised to on Friday. It was now late Saturday and she hadn't heard anything. Finally she decided to call him.
text_b_pos: Sam answered the phone.
text_b_neg: Carly ordered take-out over the phone.

text_a: School was just a disaster today. It was raining and everyone got soaked in the rain. There was also a fire and everyone had to evacuate the school. I caught a fever from being in the rain for several minutes.
text_b_pos: I've never had a worse day.
text_b_neg: I went swimming in the lake.

text_a: Jack liked to take trips on the weekends with his friends. They often liked to go skiing in the mountains. Jack theorized that this weekend would have perfect skiing weather. He told his friends to drive with him up to the resort.
text_b_pos: They rented a car and had a wonderful time skiing.
text_b_neg: He decided that he did not want to go skiing.

text_a: Neil had just arrived in Kenya. He joined a safari tour group. They saw all kinds of exotic animals. Neil snapped photo after photo.
text_b_pos: Neil composed a photo album when he got home.
text_b_neg: He was mauled by a lion.

text_a: Tim like pasta a lot. He would make it every night for dinner. One night he didn't have the sauce for the noodles. He didn't know what to do at first.
text_b_pos: Tim decided to order out.
text_b_neg: Tim decided to never eat noodles again.

text_a: Rosie's class was having a little party. She decided to make a fruit salad for everyone. She spent lots of money on the fruit and lots of time preparing it. On the day of the party she scooped a huge bowl of the fruit salad up.
text_b_pos: Rosie's class shared the fruit salad.
text_b_neg: Rosie kept the bowl of fruit salad in her fridge at home.

text_a: I use Mister Spice no sodium sauce. I am on a low sodium diet. I tried to buy some bottles online yesterday. The computer kept rejecting my order, even though the card was active.
text_b_pos: Finally the sale went through.
text_b_neg: I was happy about how easy it was to place the order.

text_a: I woke up and looked in my closet for a shirt. Everything was dirty and on the floor. I picked up a shirt to see if it smelled bad. I found a blue shirt that didn't stink.
text_b_pos: I wore the blue shirt.
text_b_neg: I washed the blue shirt.

text_a: Laura had a passion for art. She would paint everyday after class. She painted a self portrait of herself one day. She posted it online for everyone to see.
text_b_pos: Laura was pleased to show people her art.
text_b_neg: Laura never painted again.

text_a: There once was a man named John. He worked in a factory. The factory fired him for poor work. As a result, he had to find other work.
text_b_pos: John was a troubled worker.
text_b_neg: John was an outstanding worker.

text_a: Ellie had a lot of homework to do. She started with her math homework. After she had finished that, she wrote a book report. The last assignment was a study guide, which took her ten minutes.
text_b_pos: Ellie was felt prepared for her schooling.
text_b_neg: Ellie decided to skip school the next day because she was ahead.

text_a: My neighbors are always playing loud music. It's not so bad during the day. They also play it at night, unfortunately. I finally asked them if they could lower the volume.
text_b_pos: They agreed to lower the volume.
text_b_neg: They told me that they hadn't seen my cat.

text_a: Ethan loved to make Youtube videos. However, he was too embarrassed to upload any videos. One day he gained the courage to upload one. Soon he had one hundred views!
text_b_pos: Now, Ethan wanted to make and upload even more Youtube videos.
text_b_neg: Ethan decided to never make Youtube videos again.

text_a: Joe grew a big batch of peas in his garden. He brought the peas inside and shelled them all. Then he cooked them up in a big pot. He added ham, bacon, and carrots to make thick pea soup.
text_b_pos: Joe thought about working in the garden as he ate the yummy soup.
text_b_neg: Joe dumped the pot outside because he hated soup.

text_a: Tina is very tired every single morning. She does not get enough sleep because of her two jobs. Tina decides to quit one of the jobs. She now gets enough sleep to function everyday.
text_b_pos: Tina is well rested.
text_b_neg: Tina is more tired than ever before.

text_a: Farmer Bill called out the the cows in the field. The came running in for their food. Bill poured out some grains for the cows in big bins. The cows happily ate their dinner.
text_b_pos: Bill was proud of his work.
text_b_neg: Bill searched for the cows.

text_b_neg: Don was glad he wasn't nervous at work.

text_a: Jerry wanted to start a new career. He searched the classified ads for job postings. He found a desirable posting in one of the ads. He emailed his resume to the recruiter.
text_b_pos: Then recruiter set up an interview for Jerry.
text_b_neg: Jerry decided later it was easier to collect unemployment.

text_a: There was a man from kentucky. He loved a girl who lived in Louisiana. He decided he needed to move. He moved to be with his love.
text_b_pos: The man moved to Kentucky.
text_b_neg: The man moved to Texas.

text_a: A young girl named Taylor had always wanted a pet. One day her mother surprised her with a trip to the pet store. They both entered the store and looked around. Taylor had a hard time deciding which animal to adopt.
text_b_pos: Taylor finally decided on the cute little kitten in the corner.
text_b_neg: Taylor decided instead to go clothes shopping.

text_a: Fred liked mystery novels. He used to read at least one every month. When his friends found out, they all bought him one for his birthday. But unfortunately, he started getting irritated by the attention.
text_b_pos: Fred told his friends he was taking a break from mystery novels.
text_b_neg: Fred started a mystery novel book club for his friends.

text_a: Gina couldn't turn on the water hose. The spigot was without a handle. She couldn't find the handle in the house. Finally she went into the garage to look.
text_b_pos: Gina found the handle on the washing machine.
text_b_neg: Gina fixed herself some lunch.

text_a: Trent and his family left for a road trip. They packed all their suitcases and snacks for drive. In seventy two hours they would arrive in Las Vegas. When Trent took his turn to drive he fell asleep.
text_b_pos: Trent drove off road and totaled the car.
text_b_neg: The group got to Las Vegas with no issues.

text_a: David was an all around great football player. He was nervous about his next game. A scout would be there. This game would determine his future.
text_b_pos: David hoped to play really well.
text_b_neg: David really didn't care about that game.

text_a: Carry has been short her whole life. She could never reach the top shelf at the store. Greg saw her struggling to reach. He went over and helped her.
text_b_pos: They ended up going on a date that night.
text_b_neg: She refused his help and walked away.

text_a: Emmy's dad took her to chose a kitten. There were two together in a cage. She couldn't split them up! It made her sad to have to chose.
text_b_pos: Then, Emmy's dad said she could keep both kittens.
text_b_neg: Emmy left angry because she wanted a dog.

text_a: Matt started playing baseball when he was seven. Now seventeen Year's old he still had not hit a homerun. Today was not only his last game, it was also the championship. Bottom of ninth, Matt was up at bat with two strikes to his name
text_b_pos: The next pitch he hit a homerun.
text_b_neg: Matt scored a touchdown at the last minute.

text_a: My cousin asked me if there was a point in my  life that was tough. I pulled out a photo frame. The pictures showed the moments where I was in the hospital. I explained to her the fact that I used to be a leukemia patient.
text_b_pos: She cried and hugged me, admiring my bravery.
text_b_neg: She stormed out, claiming I always changed the topic.

text_a: Tony was happy to be going on his first cruise. He arrived at the docks and was ready with all his luggage. When he walked around the corner he couldn't believe the size of it. He boarded and the ship left the docks.
text_b_pos: Tony enjoyed going on the cruise.
text_b_neg: Tony was scared of the ocean.

text_a: Gina wanted to steal her mother's house key. She waited until her mother was taking a nap. She took her mom's purse to the bathroom. She removed the key from the chain quietly.
text_b_pos: Then Gina placed the purse right back where she found it.
text_b_neg: Then Gina told her mom where the key was.

text_a: David and Mia rarely got to go out since they had young children. One Friday, they were finally able to get away to see a movie. They were looking forward to it so much, but it turned out to be bad! In fact, it was so bad that they could barely contain their giggles.
text_b_pos: David and Mia decided to leave the movie.
text_b_neg: David and Mia thought the movie was profound.

text_a: Mark was starting a new job the next day. He was nervous about being around so many strangers. He barely slept any the night before due to anxiety. When he entered the building he was greeted warmly by many people.
text_b_pos: He realized he would fit in perfectly at the new job.
text_b_neg: He was fired that same day, and walked out of the building.

text_a: Ford was proud of his high GPA. He worked every evening on assignments in order to improve it. Ford's friends warned him that he was missing out on fun. Later in life, Ford became a successful lawyer.
text_b_pos: Ford was proud of his accomplishments.
text_b_neg: Ford was sad that he achieved so much.

text_a: Chad wanted to bowl a perfect game. Last Saturday he came close. He had all strikes and only needed two more. He missed his second to last one.
text_b_pos: He did not miss the last one, but was still disappointed.
text_b_neg: Chad scored a touchdown after asking his coach for advice.

text_a: Bill and Teddy were at the bar together. Bill noticed a pretty girl. He went up to her to flirt but she didn't like him. He was too drunk to talk properly.
text_b_pos: Bill and Teddy talked loudly about how stuck up pretty girls are.
text_b_neg: Bill carefully added up the column of eight digit numbers.

text_a: Nya had been asked on a paintball trip with friends. She was nervous about going. But she went anyways, hoping to have fun. She shot paintballs at her friends and laughed the whole time.
text_b_pos: She loved it so much she planned a trip for the next week.
text_b_neg: She was shot and vowed to never go there again.

text_a: The delivery man handed a package to me. I opened the box. Since nothing was inside, I tried shouting at the delivery man. He couldn't hear me and drove off.
text_b_pos: I had to call to find out what was going on.
text_b_neg: I was happy with his service.

text_a: Ted had always dreamed of being a homeowner. However, he had feared that it was a goal he would never reach. One day his father surprised him by saying he would help Ted out. Ted's father helped to split the down payment on a home with Ted.
text_b_pos: Ted was grateful to his father for the help.
text_b_neg: Ted said he didn't want to be a homeowner anymore.

text_a: Jay didn't mind driving for his friends. He always made sure they wore their seatbelt.s. Yesterday he got into an accident. Everyone was safe even if they were hurt.
text_b_pos: The insurance company determined Jay was not at fault.
text_b_neg: Jay lost his job as an airplane pilot.

text_a: Stewart tried to finish his favorite task before going to bed. He got so engrossed in it, he forgot to keep the fire going. Shivering, he pulled a bunch of blankets around himself. He became very warm and content.
text_b_pos: When he woke up it was freezing.
text_b_neg: Stewart was glad that he remembered to keep the fire going.

text_a: Jeff was walking home to only see a tornado at a distance. Jeff knew he was in danger so he went to a nearby house. He rang the doorbell and asked if he can stay until tornado dies off. The homeowner let Jeff inside.
text_b_pos: They huddled in the bathroom as the tornado raged overhead.
text_b_neg: The earthquake lasted several minutes, causing minor damage.

text_a: Paul worked as order taker at a fast food drive thru. Customers noticed he had a really nice voice. People suggested he should work in radio. Paul quit his job at the fast food restaurant.
text_b_pos: Paul got a new job as a radio dj.
text_b_neg: Paul became a manager at the restaurant.

text_a: Jane's mother made a very good apple pie. Jane always wanted the recipe but her mother wouldn't give it to her. One Christmas, she asked her again for the recipe. Jane's mother decided that she would give her the recipe.
text_b_pos: Jane was thankful to have the recipe.
text_b_neg: Jane didn't like to bake.

text_a: Neil was visiting Limerick in Ireland. There, he saw a beautiful sight. He saw the large and lovely River Shannon! After a few minutes, he agreed with the locals.
text_b_pos: The River Shannon was beautiful.
text_b_neg: That Neil was very stupid.

text_a: Marcus was just starting his first flying lesson. He was learning to fly small commuter planes. He was nervous to take the plane up in the air. His instructor helped him take off from the airport.
text_b_pos: Marcus relaxed once they were in the air.
text_b_neg: Marcus decided to learn how to fly planes.

text_a: Neil knew what he had to do on his visit to Dublin. He couldn't leave the city without visiting its many pubs! Neil saw dozens of pubs and had dozens of pints. He got very tipsy, but he remembered one thing for sure.
text_b_pos: He did not drive under the influence.
text_b_neg: He remembered to invest in gold.

text_a: I had been giving this homeless man change everyday. He was on the same corner near my house. One day, as I was driving through my neighborhood I saw a new car. Soon enough, I saw the same homeless man emerge from it!
text_b_pos: I never gave the man money again.
text_b_neg: The next day I gave the man twenty dollars.

text_a: Matt was out for a walk with his mom. Suddenly he saw something shiny on the ground. He bent to pick it up. It was a gold ring!
text_b_pos: Matt was excited to be so lucky.
text_b_neg: Matt was frustrated about what he found.

text_a: Gordon bought his son a remote control car for Christmas. But he realized that it needed AA batteries. Gordon could not find any. So the next day, he went to the toy store where he bought the car.
text_b_pos: He bought a big package of AA batteries.
text_b_neg: He bought another remote control car for himself.

text_a: Brad wanted eggs for breakfast. Brad was all out of eggs! Brad cried for a long time. Brad's mother came home with eggs!
text_b_pos: Brad had delicious Eggs Benedict.
text_b_neg: Brad hated his mother for getting the eggs.

text_a: The little sister found out she was having a baby brother. She was excited until she found out she would no longer be the baby. Then she started acting out. She colored on the walls.
text_b_pos: The little sister got punished with a timeout.
text_b_neg: The little sister was given a cookie for her behavior.

text_a: Rufus notices that he has let his fingernails grow too long. They are making a loud tapping sound when he types on his computer. Rufus decides to cut his fingernails one night. When he's finally finished, he feels relieved.
text_b_pos: His fingernails are much shorter.
text_b_neg: His fingernails are way too long.

text_a: Ned and his friends went to the fair. He used the last of his money to buy a fluffy cotton candy. As he was walking away, he saw a little boy crying. He had dropped his cotton candy into a puddle.
text_b_pos: So Ned gave him his own cotton candy.
text_b_neg: He bought more cotton candy for the boy.

text_a: Joe had an accountant. He never paid attention to his accountant. Until one day he realized he had no money. Joe furiously stormed into the accountant's office.
text_b_pos: Joe asked the accountant what happened.
text_b_neg: Joe went for a run on the beach.

text_a: Officer Dunn didn't want to hurt anyone during the protest. He told several people to leave but they didn't. He unleashed his police dog. The dog bit a mother and her baby.
text_b_pos: Officer Dunn was shocked about what his dog had done.
text_b_neg: The baby even pet the dog right afterwards.

text_a: Quinton was getting evicted from his apartment. He was broke with no income. One day, he decided to spend his last dollar on the lotto. To his disbelief, he won $50,000!
text_b_pos: Quinton was so happy.
text_b_neg: Quinton felt depressed.

text_a: Gina was at her friend Ruth's house. A girl she didn't know named Jane showed up. Jane was rude, and stuck up. Gina later discovered Jane was her enemy Joe's sister.
text_b_pos: So now she avoids Jane all the time.
text_b_neg: So she happily became friends with Jane.

text_a: Mike was sitting at his desk. But suddenly, he felt a strange itching sensation on his arm. He felt his legs become itchy too. And then his face.
text_b_pos: Mike had a stroke.
text_b_neg: Mike started laughing hysterically.

text_a: Amy, Lynn and Kim walked to the store near Lynn's house. While there they saw Lynn's crush Jim. He was a bag boy at the store. They stopped and talked to him for awhile.
text_b_pos: Jim asked Lynn on a date.
text_b_neg: Lynn told Jim the he is unattractive.
